1
00:00:00,280 --> 00:00:02,720
Nermin I'm asking where
you got the money from?

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:05,640
Yesterday, you were having
an attitude because I didn't give you money

3
00:00:05,920 --> 00:00:07,560
I took Müzeyyen's necklace.

4
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:09,160
My necklace is missing.

5
00:00:09,640 --> 00:00:11,000
Whoever took it should speak up.

6
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,240
We're not thieves, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

7
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,839
Don't try to
use that “poor man's speech” stuff on me.

8
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:17,160
Someone has entered my room.

9
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:19,320
You'd better call the
police, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

10
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:21,480
You stole it!

11
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:25,000
If stones were to rain down on
our heads, you'd still put the blame on us.

12
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:26,400
Unbelievable!

13
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:29,800
I learned that Ateş
had a brother and he died, Ziya.

14
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:31,720
Find out for me

15
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:32,840
what is his brother's name

16
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:34,600
why he died and where his grave is.

17
00:00:34,960 --> 00:00:37,440
You can’t invite guests without asking me.

18
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:39,720
You’re stupid enough

19
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:43,120
to try making some cheap, half-assed
food just to seduce Ateş.

20
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:44,560
Enough!

21
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:46,800
I told you to stay away from Mercan.

22
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:50,320
Leave before I break your heart!

23
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:54,120
If Mercan finds out why
Ateş really came here...

24
00:00:54,440 --> 00:00:56,320
His revenge plan...

25
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:58,160
Are you out of your mind?!

26
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:02,280
Never! That will never happen! Get that out
of your head!

27
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:08,160
Every part of me is in love with every part
of you.

28
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:10,480
What are you saying?

29
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:13,920
Again with these "Look at me" commands?

30
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:18,720
I’m saying you’ve taken over my heart!

31
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:22,120
I love you! I love you.

32
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,840
I love you! I love you.

33
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:29,000
Do you understand?

34
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,720
Now you know.

35
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:45,040
At the crack of dawn, in
the dead of night, at sunrise, at sunset...

36
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:51,080
This heart wants you by
its side every second.

37
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:56,480
This love broke even me.

38
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:58,760
Did he say love?

39
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,520
Did he just say he loves me?

40
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:16,080
Mercan? Aren’t you going to say anything?

41
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,800
What am I supposed to say now?

42
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:22,040
Mercan, talk to me. Come on.

43
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:28,240
Say something, don’t scare me, Mercan.

44
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,560
I...
You?

45
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:37,120
My God, help me. What is he saying?

46
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:45,880
I heard a sound from there.

47
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,080
From where?
There’s something there.

48
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:50,520
What sound? What am I even saying?

49
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:52,680
What sound?

50
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:54,480
Look, over there.

51
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:55,920
Where?

52
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,080
Mercan?

53
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,520
How could you tear us apart like this?

54
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:23,880
No. I won’t allow it.

55
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,920
Just like you destroyed my world...

56
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:30,520
I’ll destroy yours too, Mercan.

57
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,440
Çiçek.

58
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:36,600
Malik?

59
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,080
I
Have something very important to tell you.

60
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,200
Malik, did something bad happen?

61
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:49,080
Çiçek, look, I don’t
want any secrets between us anymore, okay?

62
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,320
Secrets?

63
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:55,440
Yes. That’s why
I wanted to talk to you right away.

64
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:02,439
My brother is calling.

65
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:05,320
Perfect timing, as always.

66
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:08,416
He’s acting like an inspector.
Never mind, I’ll call him later. You talk.

67
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,520
No, no, answer it. I’ll talk later.

68
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,680
It’ll ring and hang up. You talk, Malik.

69
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,840
He’ll worry. Answer, I’ll explain now.

70
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,600
Hello?

71
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:25,600
What?

72
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:32,000
Brother, what are you talking about?

73
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,120
Mom!

74
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:35,280
Mom!
Çiçek!

75
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,800
Çiçek, what happened?

76
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,040
Çiçek!

77
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,720
Where did Mr. Ateş and
Ms. Mercan disappear to?

78
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:50,720
Exactly. Where are they?

79
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:53,080
They went that way a moment ago.

80
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:56,400
I’ll check.

81
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,280
Are you okay?

82
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,400
Yes, I’m fine.

83
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,760
No bad news, Insallah? No problem?

84
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:32,880
No, no.

85
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,680
Mercan slipped.

86
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:42,080
I tried to help
her and, well, my clothes got a bit dirty.

87
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:47,280
Yes, I fell badly. It was rough.

88
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:48,640
God forbid such falls.

89
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:53,280
Amen.

90
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:59,680
Friends,
I sincerely thank you all for this project.

91
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:02,880
I appreciate every one
of you. Not every team could pull this off.

92
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,199
A round of applause for ourselves. Bravo.

93
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,200
Well done, everyone.

94
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,680
It turned out great.

95
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,719
No one gave up.

96
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:15,920
I knew from that
one-hour performance the project was ours.

97
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,600
I agree. Absolutely.

98
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,600
I don’t get what he’s trying to do.

99
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,880
My God, what’s happening?

100
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:45,080
Ateş, something happened.

101
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:49,000
Wait,
don’t panic. We’ll understand in a moment.

102
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,000
Oh God, what happened?

103
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:27,120
Thank
God it wasn’t serious. She got through it.

104
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:36,000
Don’t worry, you heard the doctor. A minor
heart spasm. She needs rest.

105
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:44,160
I wish she had stayed at
the hospital. She would’ve been monitored.

106
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,800
Nothing will happen to her, right, Ateş?

107
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:52,760
Nothing. Don’t worry. Her kids
are with her. Berat and Çiçek are here too.

108
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:58,480
And aunt Binnaz didn’t want
to stay. The doctor approved. Don’t worry.

109
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:07,560
I’m not used to seeing her so lifeless.

110
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:16,280
Aunt Binnaz is a good woman. She’s watched
over me since childhood.

111
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:26,240
I know. She seems like a good person.

112
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:35,440
Always protected me. Always handled what I
requested. My brother used to get jealous.

113
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:39,560
I was so
scared something would happen to her.

114
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:43,800
Don’t cry.

115
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:56,360
It’s over now. The kids are with
her. We’re here too. We’ll watch over her.

116
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:10,920
Sorry, I lost myself for a moment.

117
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,880
It’s fine. As long as you don’t get upset.

118
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,480
Thank you.

119
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:24,400
Is something wrong? You seem uneasy.

120
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:30,200
No. Why would there be a problem?

121
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:39,360
I don’t know. Maybe you want to
say something. Do you?

122
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:46,560
Well... I...

123
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,000
Yes?

124
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:55,360
I’m filthy. I should go change.

125
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:16,960
Why
are you silent, Mercan? You’re scaring me.

126
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:24,960
Is one word really
this hard? Either you’ll say “me too” or...

127
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:44,800
My dear, are you okay? No pain?

128
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:49,440
I’m fine, I’m fine. It was awkward
for Mr. Ateş too.

129
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:53,720
Mom, awkward how?
The man ran himself ragged for us.

130
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,880
Ms. Mercan too.

131
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,920
Don’t worry, Mom.

132
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:02,040
May God bless them.

133
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,800
I’ll get some air then.

134
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,320
I feel suffocated.
What happened, girl?

135
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:24,280
I don’t know, I feel tight.

136
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,560
Malik?

137
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:39,440
I was worried about
aunt Binnaz. She’s okay, right?

138
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:43,000
She is. Thank God she recovered.

139
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:46,760
Thank God. Our prayers were answered.

140
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,680
It’s cold. Come inside.

141
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:57,640
No, I won’t. If she sees me, there may be
trouble.

142
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,640
I don’t want to cause discomfort.

143
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:00,160
Nothing will happen.

144
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,320
It will.

145
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,839
Berat, fix that pillow.

146
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,840
Of course, Mom.

147
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:12,160
You’re okay, right, Mom?

148
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:14,960
I’m fine, son.

149
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:20,160
What happened?

150
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,920
It’s cold outside.

151
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:30,840
Çiçek.

152
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,560
Go inside.

153
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,440
What’s going on, son? I don’t understand.

154
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,160
What, Mom?

155
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,600
I said what’s going on?

156
00:13:56,360 --> 00:14:00,840
It’s cold, she’ll get sick. Let’s not deal
with that now.

157
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,000
You’re right, son.

158
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:15,880
Çiçek, boil some linden tea for us.

159
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,320
It’s my remedy.

160
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:19,360
Okay, Mom, right away.

161
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,200
Son.
Yes, Mom?

162
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,160
I gave the check to Haydar.

163
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:29,080
Mom, why did you...

164
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:35,160
Son, nothing good comes
from that man. Good never comes from evil.

165
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,839
Mom, actually...

166
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:39,080
Listen. Mom, actually...
Listen.

167
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:44,280
Neither you nor
your sibling will see any good from Haydar.

168
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,520
I don’t know how much
time I have left. Don’t leave me worried.

169
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:52,840
Keep your distance from
him. Cut ties. Understand?

170
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:55,200
Don’t upset me anymore.

171
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:59,080
Okay, Mom, okay. Don’t worry.

172
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:00,800
I won’t deal with him.

173
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:04,200
Okay,
Mom. I won’t do business with Haydar again.

174
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:08,120
You have my word.

175
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,360
My dear mother.

176
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,160
Çiçek, hurry.

177
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,560
What did you do, Mercan?

178
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:30,880
She’s fine. Thank God she got through it.

179
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:36,760
Oh, get well soon. Your
clothes are still muddy.

180
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,440
What happened between you and Ateş?

181
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:46,400
Nothing. I told you I fell. That’s why.

182
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:47,520
I’ll go change.

183
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:50,960
No, dear, you’re not
going anywhere. Something happened.

184
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:53,800
Sit down. Tell me. Don’t make me burst.

185
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,200
Something happened.

186
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:00,440
Well...

187
00:16:00,441 --> 00:16:01,800
What happened? Tell me, Mercan.

188
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,000
Ateş...

189
00:16:11,001 --> 00:16:12,440
Ateş said he loves me.

190
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:14,520
What?

191
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:24,320
Oh, Ateş, oh.

192
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:32,880
I knew it.

193
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:36,480
What did you say?

194
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:42,160
What could I say? I made an excuse and ran.

195
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:44,960
Oh, Mercan.

196
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,560
You really did that?

197
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:51,239
I was in shock.

198
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:54,520
You know our marriage isn’t normal.

199
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,240
What I’ve been through in this house...

200
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:02,279
He was always by my side, but...

201
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,280
he was different.

202
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,840
How can I forget all that?

203
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:10,520
You’re right.

204
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:14,240
When heart and mind go to war...

205
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:17,200
the heart always wins.

206
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:19,999
What will happen now, Demet?

207
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,200
How will we come together?

208
00:17:23,080 --> 00:17:26,520
Even if we survive, will we be happy?

209
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:30,759
Sometimes one should listen to reason...

210
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:32,520
to avoid pain.

211
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:34,960
So no one gets hurt too badly.

212
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:43,279
Ateş and I...

213
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:44,280
are impossible.

214
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:53,759
At least you’re not completely foolish.

215
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:56,120
At least you see the truth.

216
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:07,080
If
You see it as impossible, that’s not love.

217
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,720
You can’t measure this.

218
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:13,039
If you truly love...

219
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:15,400
you’re doomed to lose to love.

220
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:21,639
A person’s greatest defeat...

221
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:22,640
is love.

222
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,600
So you dropped the bomb?

223
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,640
But she said nothing.

224
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,320
Then she feels nothing.

225
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:13,040
No, it’s not like that. Listen.

226
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:14,560
Don’t jump to conclusions.

227
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:16,400
Give it time.

228
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:18,680
Look at the battles you fought to get here.

229
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:20,560
Let her fight her own battle.

230
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,760
Some things time can’t fix.

231
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:33,600
Look what I did to him since she came here.

232
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:39,440
The more
she stays silent, the more she’ll remember.

233
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:41,520
And as she remembers...

234
00:19:41,521 --> 00:19:43,519
you’re being unfair to yourself.

235
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:48,040
What matters isn’t sweet words.

236
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:51,160
What
matters is standing by them in hard times.

237
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:53,000
You already did that.

238
00:19:54,840 --> 00:19:55,840
Okay.

239
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,360
Let’s say you’re right.

240
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,440
She said yes.

241
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:02,640
Then what, Cemal?

242
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:07,120
How will I explain all this?

243
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,560
I think I made a mistake.

244
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:16,120
Slow down.

245
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:18,960
Let Mercan think first.

246
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:21,480
Wait for her answer.

247
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:29,720
When I said it, a weight lifted.

248
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:44,600
But another weight settled here.

249
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:47,240
My eyes ache.

250
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:53,440
What kind of feeling is this?

251
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,120
What’s wrong with me?

252
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:32,240
Ateş declared his love in the garden.

253
00:21:34,040 --> 00:21:35,040
What?

254
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:36,560
What are you saying?

255
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:42,440
While everyone chatted,
they played Romeo and Juliet.

256
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:43,920
It’s over then.

257
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:45,280
Nothing is over.

258
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:47,840
We keep trying...

259
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:48,960
but it doesn’t work.

260
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,240
What did she say?

261
00:21:52,760 --> 00:21:54,160
Whatever she said.

262
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:57,960
I have nothing left to lose.

263
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:01,560
It’s time to act.

264
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:05,320
What’s on your mind?

265
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:09,240
Something.

266
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:11,240
I’ll call you.

267
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:16,000
Don’t you dare hurt Mercan.

268
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:21,360
Do you hear me?

269
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,160
Don’t hurt her.

270
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,600
Okay, wait for my call.

271
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:33,279
Brother, let’s go.

272
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,280
Come on.

273
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:39,160
Don’t.

274
00:23:17,040 --> 00:23:18,600
I love you, I do.

275
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,400
Understand already.

276
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:41,520
What did I just say?

277
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:50,400
What did you say?

278
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:04,160
I didn’t hear you come in.

279
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,400
I noticed.

280
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,840
Why are you so quiet?

281
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:12,360
I came normally. You didn’t hear.

282
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:17,120
I was heating milk.

283
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:18,560
Want some?

284
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:20,720
No, thanks.

285
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:28,800
It’s gotten cold.

286
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:30,840
Milk helps.

287
00:24:31,320 --> 00:24:33,560
It warms you.

288
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:35,840
You thought well.

289
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:37,999
I agree.

290
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,000
Yes.

291
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:46,240
We’re covered in mud.

292
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:50,560
From rolling around.

293
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:53,920
Weren’t you going to change?

294
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:58,520
I thought I’d drink milk first.

295
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:07,720
Mercan.

296
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:14,720
You need to say something now.

297
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:18,680
What should I say? How?

298
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:24,760
You distracted me, the milk boiled over.

299
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:28,800
Are you okay?

300
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:31,360
Come.

301
00:25:33,160 --> 00:25:34,200
One second.

302
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,040
Does it hurt?

303
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:45,400
No, I’m fine.

304
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:59,520
The place is a mess. The milk’s gone.

305
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:05,400
I should go. I can’t stay like this.

306
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:06,760
I’ll change.

307
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,000
Come, girl.

308
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:32,440
Aslı?

309
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:37,000
I overheard Mercan talking...

310
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:40,680
Ateş poured his heart out.

311
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:42,840
He said he loves her.

312
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:46,120
I know, Mom.

313
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,440
You know?

314
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:54,000
I saw them. I wish I hadn’t.

315
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,920
I’m barely holding myself together.

316
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:03,040
What can we do? We lost Ateş.

317
00:27:03,320 --> 00:27:04,760
He gave in to his feelings.

318
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:08,240
But we still have a chance.

319
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:10,480
Mercan.

320
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:12,760
She’s still resisting.

321
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,919
But for how long, who knows.

322
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:16,560
She could collapse any moment.

323
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:20,080
We need to act fast.

324
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:22,120
I thought of something.

325
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:29,240
If this is about revenge, never.

326
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:32,680
Not that. Something else.

327
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:34,240
Much better.

328
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:40,360
Just like you said.

329
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:45,280
If the wolf won’t change
his path, we change the lamb’s.

330
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:50,960
Well done.

331
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:10,320
I love you.

332
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:12,360
Understand already.

333
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:43,680
Is this real?

334
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:23,440
I’m sorry.

335
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:20,560
You...

336
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:24,159
I...

337
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:24,960
You first.

338
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:26,120
No, you.

339
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,640
I...

340
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:40,120
I was going to say I’m relieved aunt Binnaz
is okay.

341
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:42,840
You’re running away again.

342
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:46,640
She got through it, thank God.

343
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:48,960
Thank God.

344
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:51,120
Death is always at the door.

345
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:53,840
Right next to life.

346
00:30:58,280 --> 00:30:59,280
True.

347
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:02,520
You never know when it comes.

348
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:07,080
Nothing should be postponed.

349
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:10,920
Say what needs saying.

350
00:31:13,160 --> 00:31:14,920
We don’t know when death comes.

351
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,120
God forbid.

352
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:20,320
True.

353
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:21,840
We need to talk.

354
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,280
One sentence.

355
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,160
You’re tired.

356
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:29,600
Lie down and rest.

357
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:30,240
No?

358
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:31,919
I’m not tired.

359
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:33,040
Lie down.

360
00:31:33,320 --> 00:31:35,040
I’m heading out anyway.

361
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:41,120
You don’t need to go.

362
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:52,679
I thought you should rest...

363
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:53,680
You rest too.

364
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:55,520
I did.

365
00:31:55,640 --> 00:31:56,920
I even changed.

366
00:31:58,080 --> 00:31:59,080
Good.

367
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:00,600
Of course.

368
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:01,880
Very good.

369
00:32:01,881 --> 00:32:03,880
You can’t sit muddy.

370
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:05,760
You should change too.

371
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:06,520
Look...

372
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:09,280
Your pants are muddy.

373
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:20,000
Ateş.

374
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:22,840
Yes.

375
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:25,760
I...

376
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:27,160
You...

377
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:34,640
How do I say it?

378
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:38,040
I was going to say let’s
check on aunt Binnaz.

379
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:39,960
It wouldn’t be proper not to.

380
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:46,960
Let’s check on her.

381
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:48,680
Let’s.

382
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:57,400
Of course.

383
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:04,480
Another cup, Mom?

384
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,680
No, enough.

385
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:06,840
Take this too.
Okay.

386
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:18,000
Welcome.

387
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:19,240
Please.
Hello, Çiçek.

388
00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:21,080
Hello.

389
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:23,200
Aunt Binnaz, please don’t get up.

390
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:25,600
I came to see how you are.

391
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,000
Oh.
Please relax.

392
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:29,920
I’m fine.

393
00:33:30,560 --> 00:33:32,160
Thank God.

394
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:34,400
That’s how it is now.

395
00:33:34,840 --> 00:33:37,240
From now on, as good as we get.

396
00:33:37,480 --> 00:33:38,480
That’s it.

397
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:39,760
Don’t say that.

398
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,880
Mashallah, what’s wrong with you?

399
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:50,480
Come on, girl.

400
00:33:57,720 --> 00:33:58,800
Welcome.

401
00:33:58,920 --> 00:33:59,920
Please.

402
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,720
Don’t trouble yourselves.

403
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:06,280
How are you?

404
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:07,760
Need anything?

405
00:34:08,640 --> 00:34:10,280
No, thank God.

406
00:34:10,680 --> 00:34:13,920
You handled everything.

407
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:21,600
Why didn’t you wait for me?

408
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:27,840
I did.

409
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:31,040
You couldn’t come out, so I came.

410
00:34:39,360 --> 00:34:40,560
May God bless you.

411
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,200
I’ll return to work tomorrow.

412
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:45,400
Never.

413
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:54,920
Zehra will handle things.

414
00:34:59,560 --> 00:35:01,680
You’re on leave until you recover.

415
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:08,440
Yes, aunt Binnaz.

416
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:10,760
If you stand up, we’ll fall out.

417
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:13,600
May God bless you.

418
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:15,720
You’re a good person.

419
00:35:17,560 --> 00:35:18,920
May God bless you too.

420
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:24,680
If you get up, Çiçek will tell me.

421
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:33,840
May God keep you together.

422
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:48,199
When you brush past death...

423
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:51,520
you see how gentle life is.

424
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:58,239
You think you have time...

425
00:35:58,240 --> 00:36:00,400
then suddenly you’re at the end.

426
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:08,560
Hold tight to the one you love.

427
00:36:09,680 --> 00:36:11,480
When your heart finds its match...

428
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:14,000
cherish it.

429
00:36:21,080 --> 00:36:23,760
Everything else is empty.

430
00:36:24,880 --> 00:36:26,800
Only love is real.

431
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:39,280
You are each other’s truth.

432
00:36:40,520 --> 00:36:42,240
Don’t let go of each other.

433
00:36:51,160 --> 00:36:54,400
I should go. Rest well.

434
00:36:56,160 --> 00:37:00,040
As I said, call if you need anything.

435
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:05,840
Get well so you can bake for us again.

436
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:11,760
Of course, whenever you want.

437
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:13,240
Get well again.

438
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:14,480
Get well.

439
00:37:15,240 --> 00:37:15,440
Thank you.

440
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:16,760
Goodbye.

441
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:17,800
See you.

442
00:37:28,240 --> 00:37:30,600
May God not separate lovers.

443
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:32,800
Amen.

444
00:37:33,320 --> 00:37:35,000
These fruits will finish.

445
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:36,600
Vitamins.

446
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:38,040
Peel them.

447
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:08,000
You are my heart’s other half, my pearl.

448
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:18,840
You are each other’s truth.

449
00:38:20,640 --> 00:38:22,280
Don’t let go.

450
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:30,400
It’s hard.

451
00:38:32,400 --> 00:38:38,200
With all these obstacles, how?

452
00:38:40,160 --> 00:38:41,960
Sometimes truth isn’t enough.

453
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:42,520
I didn’t notice you again.

454
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:46,000
You’re distracted tonight.

455
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:47,920
Why?

456
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:50,000
Did I scare you?

457
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:53,440
No.

458
00:39:55,080 --> 00:39:56,200
Nothing happened.

459
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:58,120
What could happen?

460
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:00,920
Thank you for the shawl.

461
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:05,920
It’s cold.

462
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:07,480
I don’t want you to catch cold.

463
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:13,320
You fuss later.

464
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:15,760
Not at all.

465
00:40:17,640 --> 00:40:18,720
I never fuss.

466
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:20,200
When did I?

467
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:23,120
Are you sure?

468
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:25,880
I could list it all night.

469
00:40:26,640 --> 00:40:28,880
Complaints, fussing, moods.

470
00:40:31,200 --> 00:40:32,200
Enough.

471
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:34,040
Moods?

472
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:39,920
When I’m sick, I don’t make a sound.

473
00:40:41,640 --> 00:40:43,160
Look at yourself first.

474
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:45,360
Grumpy.

475
00:40:47,680 --> 00:40:48,920
True.

476
00:40:49,720 --> 00:40:50,920
I get a bit stubborn.

477
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:58,880
And you’re a feisty princess.

478
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:02,400
Admit it.

479
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:05,440
You know yourself well.

480
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:09,640
Get out.

481
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:11,200
What are you doing here?

482
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:12,760
I said I don’t want to.

483
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:20,080
I noticed at the first hospital.

484
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:40,000
What are you doing here?

485
00:41:40,600 --> 00:41:41,600
Get out.

486
00:41:42,080 --> 00:41:43,160
Why didn’t you tell me?

487
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:44,920
Tell you what?

488
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:46,760
You gave up on marriage.

489
00:41:47,120 --> 00:41:48,120
Why didn’t you say?

490
00:41:48,720 --> 00:41:49,800
You hit me.

491
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:51,360
That’s why.

492
00:41:58,320 --> 00:42:01,160
When will news come about the art center?

493
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:02,880
It turned out well, right?

494
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:04,480
I think so.

495
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:07,040
Yes.

496
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:09,560
It really did.

497
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:12,320
Maybe we’ll go together.

498
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:19,520
Will we see spring together?

499
00:42:22,920 --> 00:42:25,240
Maybe we will.

500
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:35,440
If you want.

501
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:40,960
Want me to close it?

502
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:43,320
No need.

503
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:44,640
It’s fine.

504
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:48,039
Be careful anyway.

505
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:49,920
It’s cold.

506
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:51,800
Nothing will happen.

507
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:53,480
I’m not cold.

508
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:55,080
It’s not that cold.

509
00:42:59,800 --> 00:43:00,800
Mild.

510
00:43:00,960 --> 00:43:02,040
It feels good.

511
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:20,800
Ms. Binnaz looked well.

512
00:43:23,840 --> 00:43:24,840
Yes.

513
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:26,200
Thank God.

514
00:43:33,880 --> 00:43:35,000
Ateş... Mercan...

515
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:37,560
Yes.

516
00:43:37,800 --> 00:43:38,800
You speak.

517
00:43:39,320 --> 00:43:40,320
You speak.

518
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:50,520
Don’t you need to say something?

519
00:43:55,440 --> 00:43:58,240
I’m freezing.

520
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:00,840
Want me to close the windows?

521
00:44:06,040 --> 00:44:07,240
Or close the subject.

522
00:44:10,240 --> 00:44:14,160
If I spoke my heart...

523
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:16,320
I can’t.

524
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:19,440
Not after all this.

525
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:11,440
Maybe you’d read it easier if you turned it
around.

526
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:17,920
Maybe I read it backwards.

527
00:45:20,400 --> 00:45:21,400
Yes.

528
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:22,880
You always do.

529
00:45:31,280 --> 00:45:32,280
Anyway.

530
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:33,560
I’ll sleep.

531
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:35,160
Let me change.

532
00:45:39,880 --> 00:45:41,160
No need to force it.

533
00:45:41,720 --> 00:45:43,280
We don’t feel the same.

534
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:46,560
So I’m not his truth.

535
00:48:21,640 --> 00:48:24,040
I have so much to say.

536
00:49:10,240 --> 00:49:11,240
Good morning.

537
00:49:20,080 --> 00:49:21,080
Good morning.

538
00:49:21,760 --> 00:49:23,240
I didn’t want to wake you.

539
00:49:25,840 --> 00:49:26,840
I noticed.

540
00:49:28,440 --> 00:49:29,840
It’s early.

541
00:49:32,960 --> 00:49:34,960
I’ll go then.

542
00:49:35,440 --> 00:49:37,360
To wash up.

543
00:49:45,360 --> 00:49:46,360
Go ahead.

544
00:49:47,920 --> 00:49:49,840
Run. Let’s see how far.

545
00:49:56,800 --> 00:49:58,680
This came to you.

546
00:50:00,800 --> 00:50:02,120
Did you sort the ticket?

547
00:50:02,480 --> 00:50:03,760
I’m trying.

548
00:50:04,320 --> 00:50:07,120
This time, don’t mess it up.

549
00:50:07,960 --> 00:50:08,960
Aslı.

550
00:50:09,200 --> 00:50:10,800
I can’t afford mistakes anymore.

551
00:50:14,960 --> 00:50:15,960
My necklace...

552
00:50:30,240 --> 00:50:31,240
Yes, Hasan.

553
00:50:31,520 --> 00:50:34,520
I found the necklace you asked about.

554
00:50:34,640 --> 00:50:35,960
At a jeweler friend.

555
00:50:36,120 --> 00:50:37,360
I bought it and sent it.

556
00:50:37,520 --> 00:50:39,200
It arrived. Thanks.

557
00:50:39,680 --> 00:50:40,720
How did it get there?

558
00:50:41,400 --> 00:50:43,080
My friend said that a woman brought it.

559
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:46,240
Who sold it? Any info?

560
00:50:46,960 --> 00:50:48,600
There’s camera footage.

561
00:50:49,480 --> 00:50:50,600
Sending it now.

562
00:50:52,840 --> 00:50:53,840
Okay.

563
00:51:15,240 --> 00:51:17,400
Nermin.

564
00:51:19,240 --> 00:51:20,240
I knew it.

565
00:51:22,160 --> 00:51:23,160
I knew it.

566
00:51:34,680 --> 00:51:36,560
My threats worked.

567
00:51:37,240 --> 00:51:41,200
Nurgül left Haydar for someone else.

568
00:51:42,120 --> 00:51:43,960
Why now, after all these years?

569
00:51:47,560 --> 00:51:49,840
Maybe I’m worrying for nothing.

570
00:51:52,800 --> 00:51:54,920
The kid found the photos by chance.

571
00:51:57,240 --> 00:51:58,960
How will I know?

572
00:52:01,680 --> 00:52:02,960
Who is his mother?

573
00:52:05,120 --> 00:52:06,160
If it’s Nurgül...

574
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:07,800
Oh no.

575
00:52:11,760 --> 00:52:14,440
One trouble after another.

576
00:52:16,600 --> 00:52:19,240
What if Burak is Haydar’s son?

577
00:52:20,800 --> 00:52:23,360
What if his mother sent him?

578
00:52:24,880 --> 00:52:27,000
What if his intent is worse?

579
00:52:29,320 --> 00:52:31,640
This won’t do.

580
00:52:37,480 --> 00:52:40,360
Hello, Yaşar.

581
00:52:41,680 --> 00:52:45,399
I need all employee names.

582
00:52:45,400 --> 00:52:46,400
Urgent.

583
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:49,280
I’m waiting.

584
00:53:02,520 --> 00:53:03,520
Burak Yücel.

585
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:06,440
That’s it.

586
00:53:08,040 --> 00:53:09,720
Everyone is on social media.

587
00:53:10,560 --> 00:53:12,040
They must be there.

588
00:53:13,520 --> 00:53:14,640
Burak Yücel.

589
00:53:20,480 --> 00:53:21,480
No.

590
00:53:23,080 --> 00:53:26,800
Nurgül Yücel.

591
00:53:32,640 --> 00:53:33,880
Not there.

592
00:53:49,840 --> 00:53:50,840
What’s wrong, Nermin?

593
00:53:52,760 --> 00:53:53,760
Good news?

594
00:53:54,920 --> 00:53:57,600
Have we seen any good lately?

595
00:53:58,080 --> 00:54:01,800
Good stopped greeting us long ago.

596
00:54:02,440 --> 00:54:03,640
God forbid.

597
00:54:06,640 --> 00:54:08,320
We say hello and owe money.

598
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:12,920
Make one day match another.

599
00:54:15,080 --> 00:54:16,080
God.

600
00:54:21,200 --> 00:54:23,400
I’ll solve this.

601
00:54:24,200 --> 00:54:27,000
I’ll show you who you’re married to.

602
00:54:34,360 --> 00:54:35,600
I couldn’t find it.

603
00:54:57,360 --> 00:54:58,720
Thank God she slept.

604
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:04,760
Brother, what if something happened?

605
00:55:05,280 --> 00:55:09,280
Don’t say that. God forbid.

606
00:55:09,680 --> 00:55:12,000
God forbid.

607
00:55:16,720 --> 00:55:19,600
This is what happens when you scheme behind
her with Malik.

608
00:55:20,200 --> 00:55:21,560
That’s why Mom got like this.

609
00:55:23,480 --> 00:55:24,880
Çiçek was very upset.

610
00:55:26,440 --> 00:55:29,080
I schemed?

611
00:55:30,320 --> 00:55:33,400
That’s unfair.

612
00:55:33,840 --> 00:55:35,240
It’s your fault.

613
00:55:35,520 --> 00:55:39,240
You borrowed from loan sharks.

614
00:55:39,480 --> 00:55:42,720
I know how scared she was.

615
00:55:45,640 --> 00:55:48,560
Is a son’s debt more important?

616
00:55:49,680 --> 00:55:51,200
Or fear of losing a daughter?

617
00:55:52,000 --> 00:55:53,560
I know my mother.

618
00:55:55,120 --> 00:55:56,120
Understand?

619
00:55:56,720 --> 00:55:58,320
She was devastated by betrayal.

620
00:55:59,160 --> 00:56:02,520
I’m the only one who schemed?

621
00:56:03,640 --> 00:56:07,600
You borrowed money from loan sharks.
What about her fear of losing her son?

622
00:56:07,960 --> 00:56:08,960
You are forgetting that.

623
00:56:10,120 --> 00:56:11,120
I don’t.

624
00:56:11,360 --> 00:56:14,640
We would’ve paid it somehow.

625
00:56:15,520 --> 00:56:17,120
Who did you borrow from?

626
00:56:17,920 --> 00:56:19,120
Loan sharks.

627
00:56:40,000 --> 00:56:41,760
He’s waiting for an answer.

628
00:56:44,960 --> 00:56:46,480
What can I say?

629
00:57:06,640 --> 00:57:07,760
She slept again.

630
00:57:33,120 --> 00:57:39,480
I know I shook everything by confessing.

631
00:57:41,280 --> 00:57:44,000
I’m shattered.

632
00:57:48,040 --> 00:57:51,200
I know I pushed you.

633
00:57:55,760 --> 00:58:00,880
With our past on our backs.

634
00:58:04,440 --> 00:58:06,200
I’m not ready.

635
00:58:06,600 --> 00:58:07,600
I’m scared.

636
00:58:08,080 --> 00:58:12,280
Not of what
will happen, but of my feelings.

637
00:58:17,200 --> 00:58:19,320
I expect too much from your heart.

638
00:58:26,840 --> 00:58:31,240
If only I knew what’s in it.

639
00:58:49,160 --> 00:58:52,080
My precious.

640
00:58:58,720 --> 00:59:00,680
How can I give up your eyes?

641
00:59:09,680 --> 00:59:12,680
If only you knew my heart.

642
00:59:14,320 --> 00:59:17,120
If only you understood without words.

643
00:59:21,240 --> 00:59:22,440
I couldn’t stay silent.

644
00:59:25,640 --> 00:59:27,760
I can’t come to you now.

645
00:59:34,800 --> 00:59:35,960
But I can’t leave either.

646
01:00:08,360 --> 01:00:13,200
Silence isn’t easy.

647
01:00:15,680 --> 01:00:18,840
My mind is confused, my heart shattered.

648
01:00:23,240 --> 01:00:27,320
I’m not ready to accept or lose you.

649
01:00:29,640 --> 01:00:33,160
I don’t know what to say.

650
01:00:37,800 --> 01:00:41,480
The lock on my tongue, the key to my love.

651
01:00:44,640 --> 01:00:47,880
Regret either way.

652
01:00:55,560 --> 01:00:58,240
Something will come out
of this Burak matter.

653
01:00:58,680 --> 01:00:59,880
We shouldn’t leave it idle.

654
01:01:00,960 --> 01:01:02,200
I’ll investigate.

655
01:01:04,960 --> 01:01:07,880
Thieving snake, I knew it.

656
01:01:08,680 --> 01:01:09,720
What are you saying?

657
01:01:10,400 --> 01:01:11,800
I didn’t steal anything.

658
01:01:13,040 --> 01:01:15,040
You didn’t, huh?

659
01:01:15,520 --> 01:01:16,520
What’s this then?

660
01:01:29,040 --> 01:01:31,160
Don’t deny it. You did it.

661
01:01:38,120 --> 01:01:39,840
The thief’s daughter is here too.

662
01:01:44,240 --> 01:01:46,040
What do you say to your mother’s work?

663
01:01:46,400 --> 01:01:48,160
Teaching you to steal?

664
01:01:50,400 --> 01:01:51,520
What are you saying?

665
01:01:53,080 --> 01:01:54,920
Look at them playing innocent.

666
01:01:58,600 --> 01:01:59,960
You’re all thieves.

667
01:02:01,320 --> 01:02:04,320
Ms. Müzeyyen, that’s enough.

668
01:02:08,720 --> 01:02:09,960
She’s gone mad.

669
01:02:10,960 --> 01:02:12,640
Would I ever do that?

670
01:02:15,000 --> 01:02:17,400
Lies and slander.

671
01:02:18,080 --> 01:02:20,440
You’re all rotten.

672
01:02:20,640 --> 01:02:23,480
Standing near you dirties a person.

673
01:02:23,800 --> 01:02:25,360
What’s going on?

674
01:02:27,080 --> 01:02:28,920
We caught a thief.

675
01:02:30,080 --> 01:02:31,240
Taking her statement.

676
01:02:32,680 --> 01:02:36,959
Your wife Nermin, unable to bear poverty...

677
01:02:36,960 --> 01:02:40,080
stole my necklace and sold it.

678
01:02:45,600 --> 01:02:49,200
Honest goods return to their owner.

679
01:02:52,760 --> 01:02:55,680
You wouldn’t know.

680
01:03:02,840 --> 01:03:04,160
I’ll disgrace you all.

681
01:03:04,600 --> 01:03:05,600
All of you.

682
01:03:08,040 --> 01:03:11,920
Is
There any crime your family hasn’t touched?

683
01:03:20,040 --> 01:03:25,080
I’ll take this so you don’t sell it again.

684
01:03:29,600 --> 01:03:30,640
It’s not true, right, Mom?

685
01:03:31,600 --> 01:03:33,280
Please say it’s not.

686
01:03:37,520 --> 01:03:39,360
They’re the real thieves.

687
01:03:42,120 --> 01:03:44,440
They seized our home.

688
01:03:46,800 --> 01:03:48,680
They torment us.

689
01:03:50,400 --> 01:03:51,960
I took what was ours.

690
01:03:52,760 --> 01:03:54,960
I can’t believe you.

691
01:03:55,640 --> 01:03:56,760
Didn’t you think of me?

692
01:03:57,600 --> 01:03:59,160
Is money everything?

693
01:04:00,200 --> 01:04:01,760
Is that all we lost?

694
01:04:08,800 --> 01:04:11,160
We lost our honor.

695
01:04:13,400 --> 01:04:18,040
I lost my future for you.

696
01:04:25,520 --> 01:04:27,400
If you call it torment, call this.

697
01:04:28,280 --> 01:04:30,440
I endured their cruelty.

698
01:04:33,600 --> 01:04:35,680
Worse than that...

699
01:04:36,680 --> 01:04:41,520
is having a
family who throws their children into fire.

700
01:05:08,080 --> 01:05:09,080
Okay.

701
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:11,400
Deal.

702
01:05:12,360 --> 01:05:13,400
I’ll wait for news.

703
01:05:15,400 --> 01:05:16,400
Okay.

704
01:05:25,320 --> 01:05:26,320
What happened?

705
01:05:26,640 --> 01:05:27,640
Please let go.

706
01:05:28,200 --> 01:05:29,720
Not without knowing.

707
01:05:30,720 --> 01:05:31,960
Please, let go.

708
01:05:32,760 --> 01:05:33,760
Why are you crying?

709
01:05:34,920 --> 01:05:36,000
Did someone hurt you?

710
01:05:37,440 --> 01:05:39,840
Was it Müzeyyen? Aslı?

711
01:05:40,280 --> 01:05:42,840
No one did anything. Let go.

712
01:05:43,720 --> 01:05:45,840
How can I leave you like this?

713
01:05:47,480 --> 01:05:48,800
Let me help.

714
01:05:49,880 --> 01:05:51,360
No one can help me.

715
01:05:52,360 --> 01:05:53,360
No one.

716
01:05:53,880 --> 01:05:56,720
I’ve lived in shame for months.

717
01:05:59,760 --> 01:06:00,760
Mercan.

718
01:06:03,800 --> 01:06:04,800
Shall we talk?

719
01:06:10,360 --> 01:06:11,560
Nothing to talk about.

720
01:06:12,520 --> 01:06:14,200
I didn’t just enter this hell.

721
01:06:15,040 --> 01:06:17,200
I was already in one.

722
01:06:18,480 --> 01:06:20,799
But I saw this...

723
01:06:20,800 --> 01:06:22,000
it’s not about the Karahans.

724
01:06:26,320 --> 01:06:29,480
I wish blaming others worked.

725
01:06:30,200 --> 01:06:32,240
I wish it were easy.

726
01:06:33,440 --> 01:06:36,439
My family, my life...

727
01:06:36,440 --> 01:06:39,600
I’m just starting to see.

728
01:06:43,320 --> 01:06:46,159
All I want is to leave...

729
01:06:46,160 --> 01:06:47,840
to wash away this filth.

730
01:06:48,720 --> 01:06:50,040
I want peace.

731
01:07:11,320 --> 01:07:12,960
I handled the job.

732
01:07:21,440 --> 01:07:22,440
Thanks, Cemal.

733
01:07:24,880 --> 01:07:26,960
It doesn’t matter now.

734
01:07:29,360 --> 01:07:30,920
It matters more now.

735
01:07:49,240 --> 01:07:51,680
I was so upset about aunt Binnaz.

736
01:07:51,840 --> 01:07:53,600
I was terrified.

737
01:07:54,240 --> 01:07:55,240
But she got through it.

738
01:07:56,800 --> 01:07:58,920
Black Sea woman.

739
01:07:59,160 --> 01:08:00,160
Hard to knock down.

740
01:08:02,160 --> 01:08:03,240
Thank God.

741
01:08:09,000 --> 01:08:10,000
Zehra.

742
01:08:13,920 --> 01:08:14,920
You...

743
01:08:15,200 --> 01:08:16,640
are kind-hearted.

744
01:08:18,880 --> 01:08:20,600
Then you’re lucky.

745
01:08:21,040 --> 01:08:23,280
You’ll have a good wife.

746
01:08:25,240 --> 01:08:27,400
Yes.

747
01:08:29,280 --> 01:08:29,720
But...

748
01:08:30,160 --> 01:08:31,919
my mother...

749
01:08:31,920 --> 01:08:35,319
can’t handle surprises.

750
01:08:35,320 --> 01:08:39,520
Maybe we should shelve the wedding.

751
01:08:41,200 --> 01:08:43,200
Don’t misunderstand.

752
01:08:44,440 --> 01:08:45,440
Of course.

753
01:08:45,680 --> 01:08:48,279
You’re right.

754
01:08:48,280 --> 01:08:50,040
We’re already on a path.

755
01:08:54,840 --> 01:08:56,000
Some work remains.

756
01:08:56,160 --> 01:08:57,999
I’ll finish it.

757
01:08:58,000 --> 01:08:59,000
Then head back.

758
01:08:59,080 --> 01:09:00,080
Good luck.

759
01:09:00,600 --> 01:09:01,600
You too.

760
01:09:30,720 --> 01:09:31,720
Çiçek?

761
01:09:34,080 --> 01:09:35,240
How is aunt Binnaz?

762
01:09:35,600 --> 01:09:36,600
Better?

763
01:09:37,880 --> 01:09:39,080
Don’t worry.

764
01:09:39,600 --> 01:09:41,200
We’re talking about her.

765
01:09:41,440 --> 01:09:42,080
She’s strong.

766
01:09:42,200 --> 01:09:43,760
She’ll recover soon.

767
01:09:44,320 --> 01:09:45,400
With God’s permission.

768
01:09:49,240 --> 01:09:51,360
This is my fault.

769
01:10:11,400 --> 01:10:12,880
Ours.

770
01:10:33,720 --> 01:10:35,480
I love you, Malik.

771
01:10:38,040 --> 01:10:40,760
But our love isn’t above my mother’s life.

772
01:10:44,560 --> 01:10:47,760
I understand.

773
01:10:48,360 --> 01:10:49,599
I understand your fears but...

774
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:51,760
look what we survived.

775
01:10:51,960 --> 01:10:54,040
We’ll survive this too.

776
01:10:54,320 --> 01:10:55,320
We will.

777
01:10:55,840 --> 01:10:59,160
I promised not to upset her.

778
01:11:00,440 --> 01:11:01,920
We have to break up.

779
01:11:03,600 --> 01:11:04,880
Please don’t.

780
01:11:05,920 --> 01:11:07,080
I’m sorry.

781
01:11:08,360 --> 01:11:09,360
Çiçek.

782
01:11:09,640 --> 01:11:10,840
Please.

783
01:12:25,840 --> 01:12:27,240
One more shot.

784
01:12:28,600 --> 01:12:29,680
Look at each other.

785
01:12:39,920 --> 01:12:40,920
How will this work?

786
01:12:43,400 --> 01:12:44,400
Our lives...

787
01:12:45,040 --> 01:12:47,360
Our families won’t allow it.

788
01:12:48,800 --> 01:12:50,080
Our past won’t.

789
01:12:53,320 --> 01:12:55,039
There aren’t mountains between us...

790
01:12:55,040 --> 01:12:56,440
there are worlds.

791
01:13:01,160 --> 01:13:02,600
How will we do this?

792
01:13:04,840 --> 01:13:05,840
How?

793
01:13:53,880 --> 01:13:55,359
I removed the photo.

794
01:13:55,360 --> 01:13:56,840
You don’t have to explain.

795
01:13:58,240 --> 01:13:59,520
I want to.

796
01:14:00,240 --> 01:14:01,240
No need.

797
01:14:02,880 --> 01:14:04,840
You removed it because you didn’t want to
see it.

798
01:14:05,360 --> 01:14:06,360
What’s to explain?

799
01:14:07,640 --> 01:14:08,880
It’s not that simple.

800
01:14:09,480 --> 01:14:10,480
I said no need.

801
01:14:11,880 --> 01:14:12,880
It doesn’t matter.

802
01:14:13,880 --> 01:14:14,880
Don’t yell.
I’m not.

803
01:14:15,600 --> 01:14:16,600
Are you sure?
Yes.

804
01:14:36,600 --> 01:14:39,720
If it bothered you, why take it?

805
01:14:41,800 --> 01:14:43,399
That’s not the issue. The issue...

806
01:14:43,400 --> 01:14:44,840
What?

807
01:14:46,800 --> 01:14:47,800
Us.

808
01:14:47,840 --> 01:14:48,840
Us.

809
01:14:52,720 --> 01:14:53,840
This chaos.

810
01:14:54,600 --> 01:14:55,760
You don’t talk.

811
01:14:57,440 --> 01:14:58,440
There’s nothing to say.

812
01:15:01,280 --> 01:15:02,280
Don’t do this.

813
01:15:04,440 --> 01:15:05,480
I want to hear it.

814
01:15:18,280 --> 01:15:19,600
I opened my heart.

815
01:15:24,280 --> 01:15:27,280
Don’t you see what your silence does to me?

816
01:15:28,640 --> 01:15:30,680
Your silence...

817
01:15:33,760 --> 01:15:34,480
uncertainty...

818
01:15:34,481 --> 01:15:36,440
don’t you care?

819
01:15:38,160 --> 01:15:39,560
No, it’s not that.

820
01:15:41,040 --> 01:15:42,480
Then what?

821
01:15:43,200 --> 01:15:44,200
Say it.

822
01:15:44,720 --> 01:15:45,720
Say it and be done.

823
01:15:46,440 --> 01:15:47,640
It’s not the end of the world.

824
01:15:48,240 --> 01:15:51,960
I came to you despite everything.

825
01:15:54,800 --> 01:15:56,760
Be brave enough.

826
01:15:59,360 --> 01:16:01,200
Brave, huh.

827
01:16:02,360 --> 01:16:03,760
I’ll feel relieved?

828
01:16:04,080 --> 01:16:05,600
You want to hear it?

829
01:16:07,360 --> 01:16:09,520
You think it’s easy?

830
01:16:10,760 --> 01:16:11,880
I didn’t say easy.

831
01:16:14,280 --> 01:16:15,920
I thought all day.

832
01:16:16,640 --> 01:16:17,640
About how it will be.

833
01:16:18,360 --> 01:16:19,880
You tell me.

834
01:16:20,640 --> 01:16:21,760
Will we forget everything?

835
01:16:23,080 --> 01:16:24,880
Erase the past?

836
01:16:26,520 --> 01:16:27,679
What do you want to hear?

837
01:16:27,680 --> 01:16:29,720
It won’t make you happy.

838
01:16:31,560 --> 01:16:32,800
At least you’ll have an answer.

839
01:16:35,400 --> 01:16:37,680
Fine.

840
01:16:40,680 --> 01:16:41,680
There’s no us, Ateş.

841
01:16:49,720 --> 01:16:51,840
Do you understand? No us.

842
01:16:55,600 --> 01:16:57,120
After all this...

843
01:16:57,680 --> 01:16:59,680
being together is impossible.

844
01:17:03,480 --> 01:17:05,200
Do you understand? No us.

845
01:17:06,120 --> 01:17:08,279
After all this...

846
01:17:08,280 --> 01:17:10,000
being together is impossible.

847
01:18:19,120 --> 01:18:20,560
Yes...

848
01:18:21,960 --> 01:18:22,960
you’re right.

849
01:18:29,840 --> 01:18:30,840
There’s no us.

850
01:18:34,440 --> 01:18:35,440
Of course there isn’t.

851
01:18:37,400 --> 01:18:38,720
See, you get it too.

852
01:18:38,840 --> 01:18:40,320
You accepted it right away.

853
01:18:41,240 --> 01:18:42,240
It won’t happen.

854
01:18:42,400 --> 01:18:44,800
I mean, everything was wrong from the very
beginning anyway.

855
01:18:45,640 --> 01:18:48,640
We made a 187-day agreement after all. What
were we expecting?

856
01:18:55,120 --> 01:18:56,480
What was I expecting, really?

857
01:19:00,560 --> 01:19:01,560
What did you think?

858
01:19:09,120 --> 01:19:10,440
The fault is mine.

859
01:19:14,560 --> 01:19:16,800
We lived through everything we never should
have.

860
01:19:19,960 --> 01:19:21,520
Instead of being good for each other...

861
01:19:24,040 --> 01:19:25,440
we only hurt each other.

862
01:19:29,640 --> 01:19:31,640
There was no other way it could have ended
anyway.

863
01:19:33,720 --> 01:19:35,240
My God, what did I just say?

864
01:19:35,880 --> 01:19:36,880
Why did I say it?

865
01:20:38,360 --> 01:20:40,400
Just like we shattered everything else...

866
01:20:42,080 --> 01:20:43,560
let this break too.

867
01:20:50,400 --> 01:20:52,920
I’m
the one doing most of the damage, aren’t I?

868
01:20:57,160 --> 01:20:59,120
There was always a fire in your eyes.

869
01:21:03,280 --> 01:21:05,080
Like you were about to
burn everything down.

870
01:21:06,520 --> 01:21:11,080
I never understood the reason for
this anger, or why you hated me so much.

871
01:21:25,880 --> 01:21:27,760
You’re right about the anger.

872
01:21:35,160 --> 01:21:37,640
But I never hated you.

873
01:21:45,800 --> 01:21:46,800
I can’t.

874
01:21:51,080 --> 01:21:53,600
Then what’s
the reason for this anger that never fades?

875
01:21:57,800 --> 01:21:59,560
I had no other choice.

876
01:22:00,040 --> 01:22:02,800
All those
things we went through, all that hostility.

877
01:22:03,840 --> 01:22:05,600
How do you
just pretend none of it happened?

878
01:22:11,000 --> 01:22:13,520
The daughter of the man who took my brother
from me.

879
01:22:15,440 --> 01:22:17,760
The daughter of
the man I burned with the fire of revenge.

880
01:22:19,920 --> 01:22:23,400
I hope I don’t get
lost in the ashes of a fire I lit in anger.

881
01:22:25,800 --> 01:22:27,320
I should have vanished in those ashes.

882
01:22:30,200 --> 01:22:32,920
I should have run away the moment our eyes
first met.

883
01:22:43,320 --> 01:22:44,960
Everyone has wounds no one sees.

884
01:22:53,200 --> 01:22:54,520
It doesn’t matter anymore anyway.

885
01:23:05,560 --> 01:23:06,920
In the end, there is no us.

886
01:23:48,040 --> 01:23:49,720
I did the right thing.

887
01:23:51,080 --> 01:23:52,320
I did the right thing.

888
01:23:55,840 --> 01:23:57,840
Then why does it hurt this much?

889
01:24:04,600 --> 01:24:06,160
There was never going to be an us.

890
01:24:06,880 --> 01:24:07,880
Never.

891
01:24:14,800 --> 01:24:17,280
Why did we end up with so much bitterness?

892
01:24:55,960 --> 01:24:56,960
Ateş?

893
01:24:57,320 --> 01:25:00,560
I’m
not in the mood, Cemal. We’ll talk later.

894
01:25:02,840 --> 01:25:04,120
What time will you be here?

895
01:25:05,960 --> 01:25:06,960
Okay, my dear.

896
01:25:07,520 --> 01:25:09,080
I’m waiting impatiently.

897
01:25:14,360 --> 01:25:15,720
Where is he going?

898
01:25:16,040 --> 01:25:17,880
He practically flew down the stairs.

899
01:25:18,400 --> 01:25:20,520
Honestly, I don’t know,
Aslı. He’s probably upset.

900
01:25:21,480 --> 01:25:23,159
Mercan must have done something again.

901
01:25:23,160 --> 01:25:25,160
Not a single day without trouble.

902
01:25:27,200 --> 01:25:28,680
Looks like they’re not getting along.

903
01:25:29,920 --> 01:25:32,480
The
mother plays one tune, the father another.

904
01:25:33,800 --> 01:25:37,840
Ateş was going to hand
those to me and I’d turn them all into wax.

905
01:25:38,080 --> 01:25:40,136
Aslı, maybe you
can try to be a little more understanding?

906
01:25:40,160 --> 01:25:42,480
Look, it’s good
for the body and the mind, I recommend it.

907
01:25:42,680 --> 01:25:44,600
With you around, I’m not needed anyway, my
dear.

908
01:25:44,680 --> 01:25:45,680
Well I never.

909
01:25:46,360 --> 01:25:48,240
Who were you talking to? Is someone coming?

910
01:25:49,480 --> 01:25:51,480
Surprise. You’ll see when they arrive.

911
01:25:52,760 --> 01:25:55,160
I was going to the office. Might as well go
with Ateş.

912
01:25:55,400 --> 01:25:58,680
Wait, Aslı. If he’s wandering around the
garden, he probably isn’t planning to go.

913
01:25:59,240 --> 01:26:00,600
Fine then. Whenever he goes.

914
01:26:01,280 --> 01:26:04,320
Aslı, wait. Maybe he wants to be
alone. Come on, you and I will go together.

915
01:26:05,400 --> 01:26:06,999
Okay. I’ll grab my bag and come.

916
01:26:07,000 --> 01:26:08,200
Alright. I’ll wait here.

917
01:26:44,920 --> 01:26:46,800
You burned everything to the ground.

918
01:27:06,520 --> 01:27:07,440
Yes, Yaşar?

919
01:27:07,441 --> 01:27:08,760
Ms. Mercan...

920
01:27:09,400 --> 01:27:13,679
They asked for a revision on the
competition project...

921
01:27:13,680 --> 01:27:15,920
and said we need to handle it today.

922
01:27:18,920 --> 01:27:21,560
Alright. I’ll be at the office shortly.

923
01:27:52,040 --> 01:27:54,400
Mom. Are you feeling better?

924
01:27:56,880 --> 01:27:57,880
Not at all.

925
01:27:59,960 --> 01:28:02,080
I’m bored... watching TV all day.

926
01:28:04,200 --> 01:28:06,840
Sounds nice. You can watch series all day.

927
01:28:07,320 --> 01:28:08,440
I already am.

928
01:28:09,640 --> 01:28:13,080
This isn’t
for me, my girl. I’m used to being active.

929
01:28:13,760 --> 01:28:16,600
What is this, staring
at the TV all day, lying around?

930
01:28:16,840 --> 01:28:17,240
Laziness...

931
01:28:17,760 --> 01:28:20,600
Oh honestly, perfect for me.

932
01:28:23,240 --> 01:28:25,840
Çiçek, make us some tea at least, dear.

933
01:28:27,040 --> 01:28:29,560
No, mom. Tea is forbidden for you.

934
01:28:30,040 --> 01:28:31,120
What do you mean forbidden?

935
01:28:31,840 --> 01:28:34,080
Big Binnaz giving up tea?

936
01:28:34,520 --> 01:28:36,520
The doctor
said so, mom. Don’t you remember?

937
01:28:37,960 --> 01:28:40,960
Let me brew you some linden tea and we’ll
drink it together, okay?

938
01:28:41,600 --> 01:28:44,600
Fine, go on then.
But I’ll be back to my tea in a few days.

939
01:28:45,480 --> 01:28:48,720
I don’t think
so, mom. No tea or coffee for a long while.

940
01:28:48,880 --> 01:28:50,800
Because it’s forbidden. Alright?

941
01:28:51,000 --> 01:28:52,000
Çiçek.

942
01:28:54,280 --> 01:28:56,760
Come here, sit next to me.

943
01:29:00,760 --> 01:29:01,920
Come on, right here.

944
01:29:04,600 --> 01:29:06,000
What’s wrong, are you upset?

945
01:29:06,840 --> 01:29:08,240
No. I’m fine.

946
01:29:09,360 --> 01:29:13,280
Come on now. I can tell at a glance.

947
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:18,920
Mom, why are you staring
at me? You should focus on your own health.

948
01:29:19,880 --> 01:29:21,080
Did Malik upset you?

949
01:29:22,600 --> 01:29:24,320
Nothing like that.

950
01:29:25,880 --> 01:29:27,000
Are you trying to fool me?

951
01:29:29,160 --> 01:29:31,560
I see it. Come on, tell me.

952
01:29:32,400 --> 01:29:37,000
Nothing,
mom. You’re fine, I’m fine. That’s all.

953
01:29:37,880 --> 01:29:39,840
Look, Çiçek is coming with slippers.

954
01:29:41,400 --> 01:29:41,840
Oh...

955
01:29:41,841 --> 01:29:43,200
So, tell me. What is it?

956
01:29:46,720 --> 01:29:47,960
Well...

957
01:29:50,200 --> 01:29:51,600
Malik and I broke up.

958
01:29:52,840 --> 01:29:56,120
No one needs to be upset anymore.

959
01:29:58,000 --> 01:30:01,080
And I’m fine, mom. Don’t worry.

960
01:30:04,080 --> 01:30:10,000
You were right. Ours was like saying amen
to a prayer that would never be answered.

961
01:30:12,720 --> 01:30:16,720
Are you
sure, my girl? Not because I’m sick, right?

962
01:30:17,360 --> 01:30:19,120
I’m sure, mom.

963
01:30:20,920 --> 01:30:25,160
Don’t worry. Your
health comes first for me.

964
01:30:37,920 --> 01:30:39,200
Hey, I get jealous, you know.

965
01:30:40,880 --> 01:30:41,920
Come here, you crazy boy.

966
01:30:42,040 --> 01:30:43,320
Call the hungry girl. Call her.

967
01:30:43,400 --> 01:30:44,480
Oh brother.

968
01:30:46,920 --> 01:30:48,360
You’re so jealous.

969
01:30:49,840 --> 01:30:50,880
Alright, alright, come on.

970
01:31:11,720 --> 01:31:12,720
Was it worth it, Nermin?

971
01:31:13,280 --> 01:31:14,960
Was this disgrace worth it?

972
01:31:17,240 --> 01:31:17,920
Haydar...

973
01:31:17,921 --> 01:31:20,360
I’m already at the end of my rope. Don’t
push me.

974
01:31:22,560 --> 01:31:24,120
You threw me to the bottom of the well.

975
01:31:25,000 --> 01:31:27,240
I
Live in the same house as my son’s killers.

976
01:31:28,520 --> 01:31:29,520
Of course.

977
01:31:29,680 --> 01:31:32,080
You chase after nonsense every day.

978
01:31:33,160 --> 01:31:36,760
But I’m the one living
here with that horrible woman. Me.

979
01:31:39,120 --> 01:31:39,880
Oh...

980
01:31:39,881 --> 01:31:44,760
I just wanted to get some air, do a little
shopping, clear my head.

981
01:31:45,000 --> 01:31:46,080
Was that too much to ask?

982
01:31:46,800 --> 01:31:48,880
What you’re saying isn’t an excuse for what
you did.

983
01:31:49,240 --> 01:31:50,920
You stole. Theft is theft.

984
01:31:52,760 --> 01:31:54,440
Go on, sell me out then.

985
01:31:56,240 --> 01:31:57,640
I always supported you.

986
01:31:58,720 --> 01:32:00,040
You left me halfway.

987
01:32:01,640 --> 01:32:02,640
Bravo.

988
01:32:03,400 --> 01:32:06,239
You made people call Haydar
Yıldırım’s wife a thief.

989
01:32:06,240 --> 01:32:08,320
Is that what you expect me to support?

990
01:32:09,760 --> 01:32:10,880
So what are we then, Haydar?

991
01:32:12,560 --> 01:32:14,200
If not thieves, then what?

992
01:32:16,600 --> 01:32:19,480
Of course, mine don’t compare to yours.

993
01:32:20,880 --> 01:32:24,240
Human trafficking, arms trafficking.

994
01:32:25,840 --> 01:32:26,880
Want me to keep going?

995
01:32:28,560 --> 01:32:31,240
Don’t take me on, Nermin. Don’t.

996
01:32:32,160 --> 01:32:33,960
You’re the one who shouldn’t take me on.

997
01:32:34,960 --> 01:32:37,320
I haven’t forgotten what you did.

998
01:32:38,440 --> 01:32:44,000
Your betrayals, your infidelities. None of
it.

999
01:32:45,600 --> 01:32:47,680
Don’t dig up the past to cover your mess.

1000
01:32:50,080 --> 01:32:51,080
The past?

1001
01:32:52,680 --> 01:32:54,400
Maybe it’s past for you.

1002
01:32:55,960 --> 01:32:57,520
But for me, it’s still happening.

1003
01:32:58,880 --> 01:33:01,719
Betrayal is betrayal.

1004
01:33:01,720 --> 01:33:04,160
It doesn’t fade easily.

1005
01:33:05,560 --> 01:33:08,200
Opening old wounds helps no one.

1006
01:33:08,880 --> 01:33:10,520
I’m already up to my neck in work.

1007
01:33:11,000 --> 01:33:12,040
My God, have mercy.

1008
01:33:44,760 --> 01:33:46,360
Tear each other apart.

1009
01:33:47,200 --> 01:33:49,800
I’ll make you miss these days.

1010
01:33:56,040 --> 01:33:57,600
Look at the thief’s daughter.

1011
01:34:08,040 --> 01:34:09,760
I apologize on behalf of my mother.

1012
01:34:10,200 --> 01:34:12,600
There’s no defending what you did.

1013
01:34:14,120 --> 01:34:18,000
But if theft has no excuse, neither
does hurting someone.

1014
01:34:19,160 --> 01:34:22,440
You respond with
violence to even the smallest thing.

1015
01:34:25,560 --> 01:34:27,960
I treated you as you deserved.

1016
01:34:29,400 --> 01:34:31,320
You’ve been getting pretty
sharp-tongued lately.

1017
01:34:32,280 --> 01:34:34,296
If you’re counting on
Ateş, you’re wasting your time.

1018
01:34:34,320 --> 01:34:37,200
One day he says he loves
you, the next he turns his back.

1019
01:34:37,960 --> 01:34:39,359
He erases you...

1020
01:34:39,360 --> 01:34:41,440
You’ll see what I mean soon enough.

1021
01:34:45,240 --> 01:34:47,280
Your family is used to hurting people.

1022
01:34:48,560 --> 01:34:50,560
But believe me, I don’t hurt anymore.

1023
01:35:05,080 --> 01:35:06,080
Hello.

1024
01:35:08,120 --> 01:35:09,880
Thanks, my girl, I’m fine. How are you?

1025
01:35:12,560 --> 01:35:14,320
Don’t worry, I’m fine.

1026
01:35:16,440 --> 01:35:18,120
Yes, everything’s alright.

1027
01:35:21,800 --> 01:35:22,800
Sure.

1028
01:35:24,040 --> 01:35:26,040
I’ve been wanting to
come for a while anyway.

1029
01:35:28,640 --> 01:35:31,000
Okay, I’m heading out now. We’ll talk when
I get there.

1030
01:35:36,520 --> 01:35:37,520
Zehra!

1031
01:35:38,880 --> 01:35:40,160
Bring my coat and bag.

1032
01:36:08,920 --> 01:36:10,600
What are you doing?

1033
01:36:11,680 --> 01:36:12,680
What if I hadn’t seen?

1034
01:36:13,280 --> 01:36:14,800
What if I’d been distracted?

1035
01:36:16,040 --> 01:36:17,040
I saw that you saw me.

1036
01:36:17,920 --> 01:36:19,200
You were going without me.

1037
01:36:20,320 --> 01:36:21,840
I jumped in, what’s the big deal?

1038
01:36:22,720 --> 01:36:25,320
I don’t have time to wait for a
taxi. I need to go to the office.

1039
01:36:26,280 --> 01:36:27,280
I had no choice.

1040
01:36:27,800 --> 01:36:30,280
And you wouldn’t hurt me, I know that.

1041
01:36:32,400 --> 01:36:33,240
So...

1042
01:36:33,241 --> 01:36:34,720
You trust me then?

1043
01:36:36,560 --> 01:36:37,560
Why wouldn’t I?

1044
01:36:38,960 --> 01:36:39,960
Trust.

1045
01:36:41,320 --> 01:36:42,440
This is serious.

1046
01:36:46,880 --> 01:36:48,280
Don’t say it if you don’t mean it.

1047
01:36:49,960 --> 01:36:52,760
And I know you don’t trust me.

1048
01:36:53,200 --> 01:36:54,480
I said it because I felt it.

1049
01:36:55,400 --> 01:36:56,640
What is this sensitivity about?

1050
01:37:00,240 --> 01:37:01,960
You know exactly what it is.

1051
01:37:05,000 --> 01:37:06,000
I don’t know.

1052
01:37:06,920 --> 01:37:09,200
Looking for
bad intentions isn’t nice either.

1053
01:37:10,960 --> 01:37:12,360
I’m not looking for bad intentions.

1054
01:37:13,680 --> 01:37:15,320
I just want you to be honest.

1055
01:37:25,800 --> 01:37:26,800
When I was shot...

1056
01:37:27,640 --> 01:37:28,960
you rushed me to the hospital.

1057
01:37:30,480 --> 01:37:31,840
You stayed by my side for days.

1058
01:37:33,920 --> 01:37:36,839
When I was left to die in that pool...

1059
01:37:36,840 --> 01:37:39,560
you risked your own life for me.

1060
01:37:41,520 --> 01:37:44,280
After all that, is it strange that I trust
you?

1061
01:37:46,440 --> 01:37:48,200
I don’t need your gratitude.

1062
01:37:50,120 --> 01:37:51,840
What gratitude are you talking about?

1063
01:37:55,120 --> 01:37:56,120
Patience.

1064
01:37:57,680 --> 01:37:59,680
Don’t look at me with that anger.

1065
01:37:59,960 --> 01:38:01,000
I’m not angry.

1066
01:38:02,160 --> 01:38:03,600
Now you’re raising your voice.

1067
01:38:03,840 --> 01:38:04,960
Don’t speak to me like that.

1068
01:38:06,640 --> 01:38:08,600
How would you like me to speak?

1069
01:38:10,720 --> 01:38:13,480
Anything else you want me to do or not do?

1070
01:38:13,920 --> 01:38:14,920
Tell me now.

1071
01:38:15,720 --> 01:38:17,320
What does that have to do with anything?

1072
01:38:17,480 --> 01:38:19,600
I don’t believe you, twisting things like
this.

1073
01:38:20,320 --> 01:38:21,320
You’re so difficult.

1074
01:38:25,080 --> 01:38:26,080
I am.

1075
01:38:27,680 --> 01:38:29,440
Difficult and grumpy.

1076
01:38:30,320 --> 01:38:31,320
And wild.

1077
01:38:33,400 --> 01:38:34,400
Patience.

1078
01:38:36,720 --> 01:38:37,720
Are you coming with me?

1079
01:38:39,720 --> 01:38:40,720
I have no choice.

1080
01:38:41,520 --> 01:38:42,840
Then don’t say a single word.

1081
01:38:43,720 --> 01:38:44,720
I won’t.

1082
01:38:44,920 --> 01:38:45,920
Yeah, sure you won’t.

1083
01:38:55,240 --> 01:38:57,280
Could you drive slower, by the way?

1084
01:38:58,600 --> 01:39:00,720
Didn’t I say don’t say a word?

1085
01:39:31,960 --> 01:39:32,960
Mr. Haydar.

1086
01:39:33,240 --> 01:39:34,400
What is it? What do you want?

1087
01:39:36,520 --> 01:39:38,480
I wanted to say something.

1088
01:39:39,800 --> 01:39:41,280
I’m truly sorry.

1089
01:39:42,160 --> 01:39:43,520
You helped me a lot.

1090
01:39:44,240 --> 01:39:45,400
I’m ashamed in front of you.

1091
01:39:47,040 --> 01:39:48,720
You left me halfway.

1092
01:39:49,000 --> 01:39:50,416
Trusting you was a mistake...
You’re right...

1093
01:39:50,440 --> 01:39:51,440
Don’t interrupt me.

1094
01:39:52,680 --> 01:39:57,960
If you keep clinging to your
mother’s skirt, you won’t get anywhere.

1095
01:39:59,320 --> 01:40:02,920
Life
doesn’t move forward with words alone, son.

1096
01:40:05,280 --> 01:40:09,360
Unless you take responsibility and
act bravely, you’ll keep crawling along.

1097
01:40:10,920 --> 01:40:12,640
Let’s say fate and destiny, Mr. Haydar.

1098
01:40:17,880 --> 01:40:19,040
With that mindset...

1099
01:40:32,720 --> 01:40:34,600
Man, he spoke harshly.

1100
01:40:36,640 --> 01:40:37,920
He said with that mindset.

1101
01:40:40,680 --> 01:40:41,800
He said mother’s skirt.

1102
01:40:42,920 --> 01:40:44,400
He said no future.

1103
01:40:45,160 --> 01:40:46,320
He said a ton of things.

1104
01:40:46,920 --> 01:40:49,040
That was too much,
Mr. Haydar. That was uncalled for.

1105
01:40:50,880 --> 01:40:52,760
He dropped his words and walked away.

1106
01:40:57,920 --> 01:40:59,520
Honestly, it ruined my mood.

1107
01:41:01,000 --> 01:41:03,000
For no reason at all...

1108
01:41:04,120 --> 01:41:06,200
I’ll mow the lawn later.

1109
01:41:15,160 --> 01:41:16,560
Where are they?

1110
01:41:18,200 --> 01:41:19,280
Look at the time.

1111
01:41:20,120 --> 01:41:24,880
If only Ms. Mercan and Mr. Ateş would
arrive so we could start. I can’t wait.

1112
01:41:25,400 --> 01:41:27,080
You seem pretty eager about this job.

1113
01:41:27,920 --> 01:41:31,000
But it’s still business. It might not work
out.

1114
01:41:31,680 --> 01:41:33,560
I don’t want you to be disappointed.

1115
01:41:34,280 --> 01:41:36,200
Why would I be disappointed, dear?

1116
01:41:36,800 --> 01:41:38,360
We’ll get this job, don’t worry.

1117
01:41:41,080 --> 01:41:44,000
When Ms. Mercan
gets involved, things don’t fall through.

1118
01:41:46,080 --> 01:41:47,880
Right, Burak?

1119
01:41:54,120 --> 01:41:56,400
The
guy’s mind is fried, lost in another world.

1120
01:41:57,400 --> 01:41:58,639
He
Was like this at the mansion yesterday too.

1121
01:41:58,640 --> 01:42:01,000
He disappeared, then came back all gloomy.

1122
01:42:01,080 --> 01:42:02,080
What’s wrong with him?

1123
01:42:03,680 --> 01:42:06,320
Honestly, I don’t care much.

1124
01:42:10,000 --> 01:42:11,040
What should I say?

1125
01:42:20,840 --> 01:42:24,520
Look, he came alive. One hour like
a ghost, then Demet shows up and he’s fine.

1126
01:42:24,920 --> 01:42:26,120
Welcome, Demet.
I baked a cake.

1127
01:42:29,040 --> 01:42:30,120
I brought some for you too.

1128
01:42:33,840 --> 01:42:37,760
Thank you, Ms. Demet.
We were starving here.

1129
01:42:38,040 --> 01:42:39,200
We were wondering what to do.

1130
01:42:42,360 --> 01:42:43,360
Enjoy.

1131
01:42:49,240 --> 01:42:51,000
It’s delicious, Ms. Demet.

1132
01:42:51,440 --> 01:42:53,360
Whoever marries you hits the jackpot.

1133
01:42:59,240 --> 01:43:00,240
Here, you eat too, Burak.

1134
01:43:04,160 --> 01:43:06,480
Look how well-educated she is.

1135
01:43:06,880 --> 01:43:10,640
Cultured, educated,
and a great cook. Don’t miss your chance.

1136
01:43:11,800 --> 01:43:13,400
What kind of talk is that?

1137
01:43:13,640 --> 01:43:14,240
Seriously?

1138
01:43:14,600 --> 01:43:17,440
So a woman who can’t bake can’t be married?
Is that what you’re saying?

1139
01:43:18,360 --> 01:43:20,920
You gossip at the office too.

1140
01:43:21,280 --> 01:43:23,840
Should
we say you’re not marriage material either?

1141
01:43:24,080 --> 01:43:25,800
Put that label on you too?

1142
01:43:26,280 --> 01:43:27,920
Listen to this talk.

1143
01:43:30,200 --> 01:43:32,399
I’m not getting married anyway, Ms. Zahide.

1144
01:43:32,400 --> 01:43:34,680
They say bachelorhood is a kingdom.

1145
01:43:37,000 --> 01:43:39,720
Anyway. At least you know yourself.

1146
01:43:39,880 --> 01:43:41,040
Some people don’t.

1147
01:43:43,000 --> 01:43:44,560
Give me some of that cake.

1148
01:43:47,480 --> 01:43:49,159
I’m watching my calories but...

1149
01:43:49,160 --> 01:43:51,360
one slice won’t hurt.

1150
01:43:51,640 --> 01:43:53,400
Enjoy.

1151
01:43:55,200 --> 01:43:56,200
She’s funny.

1152
01:43:57,960 --> 01:43:59,360
I’ve never seen anything like this.

1153
01:44:06,720 --> 01:44:08,800
So it didn’t end quietly, did it?

1154
01:44:10,160 --> 01:44:12,840
Exactly, Yaşar. Bring
us some tea, will you?

1155
01:44:13,600 --> 01:44:14,720
I’m the one getting the tea?

1156
01:44:19,800 --> 01:44:21,280
Fine, I’ll get it.

1157
01:44:22,040 --> 01:44:23,040
If it’s no trouble.

1158
01:44:23,480 --> 01:44:24,720
I’ll grab some tea and be back.

1159
01:44:26,880 --> 01:44:27,880
With sugar?

1160
01:44:29,880 --> 01:44:31,120
I don’t use sugar.

1161
01:44:32,200 --> 01:44:33,200
Enjoy.

1162
01:44:33,240 --> 01:44:35,280
Thanks, Demet. It’s delicious.

1163
01:44:43,120 --> 01:44:44,160
Your coffees are ready.

1164
01:44:44,400 --> 01:44:46,120
Thanks a lot.

1165
01:44:46,400 --> 01:44:47,400
Aslı?

1166
01:44:47,520 --> 01:44:48,640
Thanks.

1167
01:44:52,080 --> 01:44:54,520
Ateş is here. He’s waiting
for us for the meeting. Come on.

1168
01:44:55,600 --> 01:44:57,840
You go ahead. I’m coming.

1169
01:45:01,760 --> 01:45:02,760
Alright, suit yourself.

1170
01:45:13,120 --> 01:45:15,159
Why aren’t you answering my calls?

1171
01:45:15,160 --> 01:45:16,160
No, I’m calling...

1172
01:45:16,400 --> 01:45:18,840
I was busy. Do I have to return every call?

1173
01:45:19,080 --> 01:45:20,960
Your plan with your mother backfired.

1174
01:45:21,640 --> 01:45:24,160
You said Ateş
wouldn’t accept it, but you were wrong.

1175
01:45:25,480 --> 01:45:29,280
Maybe without your mother’s plan, he wouldn’t
have realized how much he trusts his wife.

1176
01:45:29,760 --> 01:45:31,880
You can’t stir chaos and disappear.

1177
01:45:32,920 --> 01:45:36,960
Stop complaining like
a child. I have a plan. Be patient.

1178
01:45:39,120 --> 01:45:44,520
If we can’t shake Ateş’s trust in
Mercan, we’ll shake Mercan’s trust in Ateş.

1179
01:45:46,480 --> 01:45:49,320
I’ll show Mercan that
Ateş isn’t trustworthy.

1180
01:45:51,280 --> 01:45:52,280
How exactly?

1181
01:45:53,640 --> 01:45:56,880
Women like
Mercan stay away from men they don’t trust.

1182
01:45:57,840 --> 01:45:58,840
You know that well.

1183
01:46:02,560 --> 01:46:03,560
True.

1184
01:46:04,480 --> 01:46:06,120
Trust comes first for Mercan.

1185
01:46:07,440 --> 01:46:11,000
Exactly. We’ll undermine it a bit.

1186
01:46:12,480 --> 01:46:13,880
Maybe more than a bit.

1187
01:46:16,920 --> 01:46:23,240
If we steer things before Mercan gives her
heart to him, it’ll end before it begins.

1188
01:46:24,840 --> 01:46:27,160
Things are already
messy. One minuteood, one minute bad.

1189
01:46:28,960 --> 01:46:30,440
You’re right. No breathing room.

1190
01:46:32,880 --> 01:46:37,120
I won’t give any. This war will continue.

1191
01:46:39,840 --> 01:46:44,120
And I’ll win. Thanks to me, and to you of
course.

1192
01:47:03,720 --> 01:47:06,800
Was saying “there’s no us” too harsh?

1193
01:47:14,200 --> 01:47:17,160
He’s not even looking. Should I apologize?

1194
01:47:18,200 --> 01:47:22,320
No, I shouldn’t. After what he said in the
garden...

1195
01:47:38,680 --> 01:47:40,840
You’re not
uncomfortable being alone with me, are you?

1196
01:47:41,560 --> 01:47:42,560
Why would I be?

1197
01:47:43,800 --> 01:47:46,440
I don’t know. I didn’t want to bother you.

1198
01:47:48,000 --> 01:47:49,240
He’s sulking, plain and simple.

1199
01:47:55,880 --> 01:48:01,040
I’ll stop by my room, then grab coffee and
come to yours.

1200
01:48:03,280 --> 01:48:04,320
Want coffee too?

1201
01:48:13,520 --> 01:48:14,520
King of sulking.

1202
01:49:00,280 --> 01:49:03,000
Didn’t they teach you
to knock before entering?

1203
01:49:05,040 --> 01:49:09,040
You’re awfully full of yourself
for someone raised by a thief of a mother.

1204
01:49:11,280 --> 01:49:13,760
Anyone would think you’re a princess.

1205
01:49:15,000 --> 01:49:17,880
I can’t
stand your negativity. Get out of my room.

1206
01:49:19,720 --> 01:49:24,600
Look at the attitude.
Who are you kicking out of whose company?

1207
01:49:27,840 --> 01:49:28,840
Will you leave?

1208
01:49:31,320 --> 01:49:34,120
Ateş defended you
once or twice and now you’ve got courage.

1209
01:49:35,840 --> 01:49:40,160
Take
my word for it. Don’t trust him too much.

1210
01:49:42,440 --> 01:49:45,520
For him, one goes, another comes.

1211
01:49:47,920 --> 01:49:49,040
I really don’t believe you.

1212
01:49:50,440 --> 01:49:52,960
You
act like we forced our way into your life.

1213
01:49:54,320 --> 01:49:57,640
I didn’t want this marriage.
Ateş imposed it.

1214
01:49:58,880 --> 01:50:02,680
And believe me, I’m counting
the days until you’re gone from our lives.

1215
01:50:04,000 --> 01:50:09,640
Either way, you’re the ones who
benefit, yet we hear all the insults.

1216
01:50:11,000 --> 01:50:12,760
Get out of my room now.

1217
01:50:27,080 --> 01:50:29,240
Every time I see this woman, I shiver.

1218
01:50:31,960 --> 01:50:33,120
Did she spit her venom again?

1219
01:50:34,000 --> 01:50:35,440
Same as always.

1220
01:50:36,800 --> 01:50:38,040
Did you talk to Ateş?

1221
01:50:40,760 --> 01:50:41,760
Yes.

1222
01:50:43,200 --> 01:50:44,200
I did.

1223
01:50:48,840 --> 01:50:49,840
I said no.

1224
01:50:54,920 --> 01:50:56,560
I told him there’s no us.

1225
01:50:59,400 --> 01:51:00,920
I don’t know if I did the right thing.

1226
01:51:02,520 --> 01:51:06,880
If you regret it, could
it be you have feelings for him, Mercan?

1227
01:51:10,360 --> 01:51:16,280
Impossible. I guess I
regret speaking harshly, that’s all.

1228
01:51:16,360 --> 01:51:18,360
Nothing else.

1229
01:52:03,200 --> 01:52:06,240
Well, Ateş is waiting. I should go.

1230
01:52:06,920 --> 01:52:08,200
Thanks for the cake, by the way.

1231
01:52:39,320 --> 01:52:40,320
What do you want?

1232
01:52:41,520 --> 01:52:44,520
If you’re here to cause trouble, I’m not
in the mood.

1233
01:52:44,760 --> 01:52:46,000
I’m not here to cause trouble.

1234
01:52:46,400 --> 01:52:48,240
You already fill that quota for me.

1235
01:52:53,760 --> 01:52:55,320
I’m here for work.

1236
01:52:56,280 --> 01:53:00,560
We need to set personal
issues aside and focus on the project.

1237
01:53:02,760 --> 01:53:05,520
I arranged some work on the project I’m a
partner in.

1238
01:53:07,480 --> 01:53:11,000
Take a look, then we’ll talk details.

1239
01:53:17,080 --> 01:53:19,960
Talk to the project manager, not me.

1240
01:53:20,400 --> 01:53:21,720
I will. I’ll talk to both.

1241
01:53:26,720 --> 01:53:28,320
Thank you.

1242
01:53:28,840 --> 01:53:29,920
You’re welcome.

1243
01:53:34,600 --> 01:53:35,600
Hello.

1244
01:53:36,440 --> 01:53:37,440
Hello.

1245
01:53:38,640 --> 01:53:39,640
Are you okay?

1246
01:53:42,400 --> 01:53:43,600
You look tense.

1247
01:53:45,720 --> 01:53:49,599
No, I’m fine. Not tense at all.

1248
01:53:49,600 --> 01:53:51,120
Come on, Mercan.

1249
01:53:51,680 --> 01:53:55,720
I’ve known you too long so I
can understand if there is an issue or not.

1250
01:53:56,360 --> 01:53:58,800
My God, I guess this is my test.

1251
01:54:04,480 --> 01:54:07,520
Thanks for your concern, but I’m fine.

1252
01:54:09,160 --> 01:54:11,680
You and your family have
suffered enough already.

1253
01:54:15,400 --> 01:54:16,680
Just be patient a little longer.

1254
01:54:21,040 --> 01:54:22,920
They say numbered days pass quickly.

1255
01:54:29,040 --> 01:54:30,920
When it’s over, you’ll breathe easy too.

1256
01:54:31,120 --> 01:54:32,120
Trust me.

1257
01:55:03,360 --> 01:55:05,320
This man is really testing my patience.

1258
01:55:09,720 --> 01:55:13,000
I don’t want to say anything. You get too
tense.

1259
01:55:16,320 --> 01:55:17,400
I won’t. Don’t worry.

1260
01:55:21,960 --> 01:55:23,360
Because none of this is your fault.

1261
01:55:26,960 --> 01:55:27,960
Don’t look like that.

1262
01:55:29,600 --> 01:55:32,520
It’s because you brought coffee. It counts
for something.

1263
01:55:35,080 --> 01:55:38,320
Then I’ll bring coffee every morning.

1264
01:55:41,840 --> 01:55:42,840
Tea tomorrow.

1265
01:55:45,280 --> 01:55:46,600
Okay, tea.

1266
01:55:52,040 --> 01:55:56,200
I guess he won’t make an issue of it.
I don’t want problems between us anyway.

1267
01:55:59,240 --> 01:56:00,520
There wasn’t a problem, right?

1268
01:56:03,680 --> 01:56:07,920
Did I say anything? Did I say problem?

1269
01:56:08,840 --> 01:56:11,320
I meant the project.

1270
01:56:13,600 --> 01:56:15,120
Okay, I misunderstood.

1271
01:56:17,120 --> 01:56:19,560
There’s no issue with the project, right?

1272
01:56:19,880 --> 01:56:21,200
No, no. Everything’s fine.

1273
01:56:22,560 --> 01:56:24,280
Okay, let’s start then.

1274
01:56:25,280 --> 01:56:26,280
Let’s start.

1275
01:56:29,360 --> 01:56:31,160
You became my fate.

1276
01:56:32,040 --> 01:56:34,160
Can one erase fate from the heart?

1277
01:56:38,480 --> 01:56:40,120
My heart is in your hands.

1278
01:56:41,120 --> 01:56:44,600
And your hands are in the fire.

1279
01:56:54,360 --> 01:56:55,480
Let’s finish this.

1280
01:57:38,560 --> 01:57:40,800
Mehtap, my dear, how are you?

1281
01:57:41,960 --> 01:57:43,560
I hadn’t heard your voice in ages.

1282
01:57:43,960 --> 01:57:45,200
I’m fine. How are you?

1283
01:57:46,680 --> 01:57:50,080
Thanks, dear.
Don’t ask. We’re going through hard times.

1284
01:57:51,800 --> 01:57:54,359
I stopped by the office the other day...

1285
01:57:54,360 --> 01:57:57,120
chatted briefly with a few people.

1286
01:57:57,360 --> 01:57:58,560
We mentioned you.

1287
01:57:58,960 --> 01:58:00,280
You crossed my mind.

1288
01:58:01,440 --> 01:58:03,160
Time flies, doesn’t it?

1289
01:58:03,600 --> 01:58:06,000
It really does. But you haven’t changed at
all.

1290
01:58:06,160 --> 01:58:07,920
I saw your photo at an event the other day.

1291
01:58:08,040 --> 01:58:09,080
You’re still the same.

1292
01:58:09,480 --> 01:58:11,120
Thank you, sweetheart.

1293
01:58:12,720 --> 01:58:14,400
Mehtap, I want to ask you about someone.

1294
01:58:15,960 --> 01:58:17,840
You might remember Nurgül.

1295
01:58:19,920 --> 01:58:21,280
Haydar’s secretary.

1296
01:58:22,160 --> 01:58:23,520
Yes, I remember.

1297
01:58:26,160 --> 01:58:27,240
Do you have her number?

1298
01:58:28,200 --> 01:58:30,400
Nurgül passed away five
years ago, Ms. Nermin.

1299
01:58:30,800 --> 01:58:32,760
I heard it by chance from someone else.

1300
01:58:35,000 --> 01:58:36,160
Is that so?

1301
01:58:37,400 --> 01:58:38,400
I’m sorry to hear that.

1302
01:58:39,720 --> 01:58:41,640
She had a child, I think.

1303
01:58:42,760 --> 01:58:43,760
A son, Burak maybe?

1304
01:58:44,160 --> 01:58:46,440
I don’t know. We weren’t close.

1305
01:58:47,360 --> 01:58:49,720
I see.

1306
01:58:53,200 --> 01:58:54,280
Thank you.

1307
01:59:14,440 --> 01:59:16,640
I brought you soup.

1308
01:59:20,440 --> 01:59:23,000
I made it myself.

1309
01:59:24,080 --> 01:59:26,080
Why did you trouble yourself, dear?

1310
01:59:26,840 --> 01:59:28,040
What trouble?

1311
01:59:28,880 --> 01:59:31,719
I brought soup, fruit, and herbal tea.

1312
01:59:31,720 --> 01:59:34,240
First you’ll drink the soup while it’s hot.

1313
01:59:34,520 --> 01:59:36,200
Then fruit for dessert.

1314
01:59:36,480 --> 01:59:38,200
Then herbal tea.

1315
01:59:40,000 --> 01:59:41,000
You know what?

1316
01:59:42,080 --> 01:59:43,960
The mansion has no joy without you.

1317
01:59:44,880 --> 01:59:47,680
Please stand up,
bring some life back to this place.

1318
01:59:48,280 --> 01:59:49,760
But I’m not hungry.

1319
01:59:50,160 --> 01:59:53,720
You are. You’re sick, that’s why you don’t
feel like eating.

1320
01:59:54,400 --> 01:59:56,280
If you don’t eat, you won’t recover.

1321
01:59:58,640 --> 02:00:02,880
If you don’t
eat these, I won’t move an inch from here.

1322
02:00:03,760 --> 02:00:06,160
But I’m really not hungry.

1323
02:00:07,120 --> 02:00:10,720
Fine then. I’ll wait here until you eat.

1324
02:00:12,360 --> 02:00:13,960
Here.

1325
02:00:15,080 --> 02:00:16,120
I’ll drink the herbal tea.

1326
02:00:16,880 --> 02:00:19,200
No, the order matters. Soup first.

1327
02:00:20,800 --> 02:00:22,320
Soup first.

1328
02:00:29,400 --> 02:00:30,480
Drink up.

1329
02:00:32,920 --> 02:00:34,880
Well? How is it?

1330
02:00:36,320 --> 02:00:38,920
Very good. I’ll manage.

1331
02:00:40,920 --> 02:00:44,120
I made it spicy. Smells great. Made with my
own hands.

1332
02:00:44,280 --> 02:00:47,000
I really put effort into it. For healing.

1333
02:00:47,720 --> 02:00:49,240
I’ll handle it. Thanks.

1334
02:00:49,640 --> 02:00:51,560
I’ll bring tarhana soup tonight.

1335
02:00:53,360 --> 02:00:54,759
Or maybe bone broth?

1336
02:00:54,760 --> 02:00:58,000
Lots of black pepper,
nice and soothing. Which do you want?

1337
02:00:59,240 --> 02:01:03,360
No, dear. Don’t trouble yourself. You have
plenty to do here.

1338
02:01:03,840 --> 02:01:07,920
Don’t neglect your work. I don’t want
Ms. Müzeyyen upset with you because of me.

1339
02:01:08,560 --> 02:01:11,080
Okay. I’ll go now.

1340
02:01:12,240 --> 02:01:13,240
But I’ll be back.

1341
02:01:15,960 --> 02:01:20,680
I’m not
as good as you, but my hands are tasty too.

1342
02:01:21,400 --> 02:01:22,400
You can tell.

1343
02:01:23,200 --> 02:01:25,400
Don’t feel alone, alright?

1344
02:01:26,440 --> 02:01:32,200
God forbid something
happens. I haven’t slept for days.

1345
02:01:32,520 --> 02:01:33,520
I’ve been so worried.

1346
02:01:35,600 --> 02:01:38,280
Don’t worry
about work either. I’m handling everything.

1347
02:01:39,160 --> 02:01:41,960
I’m even doing extra to avoid problems.

1348
02:01:42,760 --> 02:01:45,800
So don’t worry. We’ve got it covered.

1349
02:01:48,800 --> 02:01:50,439
Drink.

1350
02:01:50,440 --> 02:01:51,600
Okay, I am.

1351
02:01:58,400 --> 02:02:03,200
Once I marry Berat, then I’ll see that face
of yours.

1352
02:02:07,600 --> 02:02:08,600
I’m going.

1353
02:02:09,640 --> 02:02:12,360
Take care.

1354
02:02:19,200 --> 02:02:20,720
Well I never.

1355
02:02:21,520 --> 02:02:22,520
What is this now?

1356
02:02:23,760 --> 02:02:26,320
She couldn’t kill me with words.

1357
02:02:27,480 --> 02:02:28,800
Will she try with soup?

1358
02:02:31,360 --> 02:02:34,360
What kind of soup is this?

1359
02:02:36,440 --> 02:02:38,520
Never mind, I’ll eat the fruit.

1360
02:02:43,280 --> 02:02:44,840
This is bad too.

1361
02:02:47,680 --> 02:02:49,640
What kind of herbal tea is this?

1362
02:02:52,840 --> 02:02:53,840
Linden?

1363
02:02:59,200 --> 02:03:01,000
Oh, this is good.

1364
02:03:02,160 --> 02:03:03,160
Sage?

1365
02:03:07,840 --> 02:03:09,040
Must be marshmallow flower.

1366
02:03:10,000 --> 02:03:11,440
Okay, I’ll drink this.

1367
02:03:13,440 --> 02:03:14,440
Well I never.

1368
02:03:23,600 --> 02:03:24,960
What do you say about this change?

1369
02:03:27,080 --> 02:03:28,160
What change?

1370
02:03:31,240 --> 02:03:32,880
Aren’t you listening?

1371
02:03:40,280 --> 02:03:42,240
Shall we take a break?

1372
02:03:42,840 --> 02:03:43,840
We could cancel.

1373
02:03:48,960 --> 02:03:50,320
Pull out and be done with it.

1374
02:03:50,560 --> 02:03:51,560
It’s just a project.

1375
02:03:52,360 --> 02:03:53,360
Not that important.

1376
02:03:55,560 --> 02:03:56,680
That’s not possible.

1377
02:03:57,400 --> 02:03:58,880
We can’t abandon what we started.

1378
02:04:00,120 --> 02:04:01,200
The team worked hard.

1379
02:04:01,840 --> 02:04:04,000
Leaving them halfway wouldn’t be right.

1380
02:04:06,920 --> 02:04:07,920
I mean...

1381
02:04:08,520 --> 02:04:10,560
I’ve never seen you this unfocused.

1382
02:04:11,800 --> 02:04:13,560
Even on days you were furious at me.

1383
02:04:19,680 --> 02:04:21,920
This morning seems to have distracted you.

1384
02:04:25,960 --> 02:04:27,920
I never want you upset because of me.

1385
02:04:32,440 --> 02:04:34,040
What I told you...

1386
02:04:34,600 --> 02:04:35,760
even I forgot.

1387
02:04:36,560 --> 02:04:37,840
Pretend you never heard it.

1388
02:04:42,840 --> 02:04:45,000
I don’t even know if I want to forget.

1389
02:04:46,000 --> 02:04:49,440
After all that hurt, I should hate you.

1390
02:04:49,760 --> 02:04:51,040
But I can’t.

1391
02:04:55,520 --> 02:04:59,080
Every
time I look into your eyes, my heart races.

1392
02:04:59,800 --> 02:05:01,920
How
did you turn everything I knew upside down?

1393
02:05:04,600 --> 02:05:06,080
This topic won’t be brought up again.

1394
02:05:07,000 --> 02:05:10,600
Don’t feel obliged to say or do anything.

1395
02:05:19,000 --> 02:05:20,240
Please don’t cry.

1396
02:05:22,240 --> 02:05:25,720
I don’t want you feeling guilty for saying
no.

1397
02:05:29,280 --> 02:05:31,960
I’m not... guilty.

1398
02:05:33,080 --> 02:05:34,080
Then what?

1399
02:05:38,040 --> 02:05:39,040
Why are you crying?

1400
02:05:51,520 --> 02:05:53,920
I... well...

1401
02:05:55,560 --> 02:05:58,920
I have so much work to do.

1402
02:06:09,720 --> 02:06:11,480
My God, keep my mind steady.

1403
02:06:13,840 --> 02:06:17,440
After being so close for so
long, how will I endure being this distant?

1404
02:06:18,520 --> 02:06:23,640
Same room, right beside me, in my mind, in
my heart...

1405
02:06:35,080 --> 02:06:37,960
Mercan ran past me. What
now, another question?

1406
02:06:42,120 --> 02:06:44,040
There really is no us, Cemal.

1407
02:06:48,480 --> 02:06:49,480
There really isn’t.

1408
02:07:51,000 --> 02:07:52,000
Malik.

1409
02:07:56,520 --> 02:08:00,280
Well... I...

1410
02:08:03,000 --> 02:08:05,520
Son, were you going to
leave without knocking?

1411
02:08:06,320 --> 02:08:08,840
I wanted to see you actually.

1412
02:08:12,120 --> 02:08:14,880
But I didn’t want to disturb you.

1413
02:08:15,520 --> 02:08:17,760
Please don’t see this as disrespect.

1414
02:08:18,280 --> 02:08:20,640
God forbid, son. What disrespect?

1415
02:08:22,200 --> 02:08:26,520
How are you, aunt Binnaz? You look
well. How do you feel?

1416
02:08:28,800 --> 02:08:32,240
I’m fine, thank God. Azrael hasn’t taken
me yet.

1417
02:08:33,640 --> 02:08:35,920
Our time isn’t up yet, let’s say.

1418
02:08:36,280 --> 02:08:39,680
Insallah that
day comes late. What kind of talk is that?

1419
02:08:40,000 --> 02:08:41,000
Amin.

1420
02:08:41,480 --> 02:08:45,560
When death knocks, it
doesn’t care for words.

1421
02:08:46,280 --> 02:08:47,600
Seems we still have days to see.

1422
02:08:48,720 --> 02:08:51,080
May God keep you with your loved ones.

1423
02:08:52,160 --> 02:08:54,320
Amin. May God keep you too, son.

1424
02:08:55,160 --> 02:08:55,760
Thank you.

1425
02:08:56,160 --> 02:08:57,280
Your parents too.

1426
02:08:57,960 --> 02:08:59,720
So, how are you, son?

1427
02:09:02,480 --> 02:09:05,960
I’m fine, thank you.
Thank you, aunt Binnaz.

1428
02:09:07,640 --> 02:09:10,120
As I said, I wanted to see you.

1429
02:09:10,600 --> 02:09:13,600
If you need anything, I’m around.

1430
02:09:14,520 --> 02:09:15,520
Please let me know.

1431
02:09:23,360 --> 02:09:26,600
Aunt Binnaz, I’m truly
sorry for everything.

1432
02:09:31,320 --> 02:09:32,760
Please forgive me.

1433
02:09:34,760 --> 02:09:35,760
You’re forgiven.

1434
02:09:37,760 --> 02:09:43,000
I bought these flowers for you.

1435
02:09:44,760 --> 02:09:46,800
Let me present them properly.

1436
02:09:57,920 --> 02:10:01,119
Once again, get well soon. May God not put
you through this again.

1437
02:10:01,120 --> 02:10:04,240
I kept you standing too long. Please rest.

1438
02:10:06,480 --> 02:10:08,200
Rest well, aunt Binnaz.

1439
02:10:10,000 --> 02:10:11,120
Thank you, my child.

1440
02:11:50,880 --> 02:11:51,880
Yes, Demet?

1441
02:11:53,200 --> 02:11:57,360
Mercan, are you okay?
You rushed past, I got worried.

1442
02:11:57,920 --> 02:11:58,920
Did something bad happen?

1443
02:12:00,080 --> 02:12:01,360
I’m fine. Don’t worry.

1444
02:12:03,440 --> 02:12:05,560
I went out for some air.

1445
02:12:11,320 --> 02:12:15,280
I
Have something to do. Something important.

1446
02:12:16,560 --> 02:12:18,160
Okay, I’m glad you’re fine.

1447
02:12:19,040 --> 02:12:20,040
I’ll be back soon.

1448
02:12:33,520 --> 02:12:36,000
Maybe I can fix my mistake.

1449
02:12:37,280 --> 02:12:39,080
Maybe then...

1450
02:12:58,720 --> 02:12:59,920
Berat.

1451
02:13:01,480 --> 02:13:02,480
Zehra.

1452
02:13:03,360 --> 02:13:05,120
I
Fixed things with your mother quite a bit.

1453
02:13:06,120 --> 02:13:07,120
When did that happen?

1454
02:13:07,280 --> 02:13:08,280
Just now.

1455
02:13:08,720 --> 02:13:09,720
Seriously?

1456
02:13:10,440 --> 02:13:14,280
I made soup and took it
to her. We’re like mother and daughter now.

1457
02:13:15,280 --> 02:13:16,280
Really?

1458
02:13:17,120 --> 02:13:18,880
Soup.

1459
02:13:19,760 --> 02:13:20,760
She drank it.

1460
02:13:21,160 --> 02:13:22,160
She drank it.

1461
02:13:22,400 --> 02:13:23,400
She finished it.

1462
02:13:24,400 --> 02:13:25,200
She finished it.

1463
02:13:25,201 --> 02:13:26,320
Did she like it?

1464
02:13:27,320 --> 02:13:28,960
Of course she did.

1465
02:13:31,000 --> 02:13:36,400
What a
question. Who wouldn’t like what you make?

1466
02:13:37,240 --> 02:13:38,240
Right?

1467
02:13:39,120 --> 02:13:40,920
I said I’d bring soup again tonight.

1468
02:13:43,640 --> 02:13:44,640
Tonight?
Tonight.

1469
02:13:46,160 --> 02:13:47,200
This evening?
This evening.

1470
02:13:49,040 --> 02:13:49,560
What did she say?

1471
02:13:49,920 --> 02:13:51,320
What would she say?

1472
02:13:51,400 --> 02:13:54,680
Berat,
you should have seen her. She was so happy.

1473
02:13:54,840 --> 02:13:57,320
So pleased, she told me to come again.

1474
02:14:00,080 --> 02:14:01,400
Thank God.

1475
02:14:01,800 --> 02:14:03,376
Thank God, everything’s falling into place.

1476
02:14:03,400 --> 02:14:04,400
Mashallah.

1477
02:14:04,760 --> 02:14:05,760
Mashallah.

1478
02:14:05,920 --> 02:14:07,000
May the evil eye stay away.

1479
02:14:08,720 --> 02:14:09,400
Mashallah.

1480
02:14:09,600 --> 02:14:10,856
My God, protect us from the evil eye.

1481
02:14:10,880 --> 02:14:11,880
Mashallah.

1482
02:14:12,000 --> 02:14:13,000
Mashallah.

1483
02:14:16,520 --> 02:14:18,079
She’s my mother now too.

1484
02:14:18,080 --> 02:14:21,240
Caring for her is my duty.

1485
02:14:24,400 --> 02:14:25,400
Thank you, Zehra.

1486
02:14:26,600 --> 02:14:28,200
You made me so happy.

1487
02:14:28,400 --> 02:14:29,400
It’s nothing, my love.

1488
02:14:33,560 --> 02:14:34,560
My love.

1489
02:14:37,280 --> 02:14:42,000
But Zehra, my mother is
very important to me.

1490
02:14:43,080 --> 02:14:45,480
Her accepting you meant a lot.

1491
02:14:46,360 --> 02:14:47,360
Thank God.

1492
02:14:47,920 --> 02:14:50,800
But I didn’t do this just to be accepted.

1493
02:14:56,640 --> 02:14:58,520
I know.

1494
02:14:58,760 --> 02:14:59,840
I know, my love.

1495
02:15:00,120 --> 02:15:01,720
I know you didn’t.

1496
02:15:02,960 --> 02:15:05,840
Berat, I value your mother deeply.

1497
02:15:07,560 --> 02:15:08,880
Mothers are precious.

1498
02:15:09,520 --> 02:15:10,520
I mean...

1499
02:15:11,000 --> 02:15:12,800
I
Know what it’s like to grow up without one.

1500
02:15:21,800 --> 02:15:23,520
My queen, my beautiful one.

1501
02:15:24,440 --> 02:15:25,720
Listen, I’ll tell you something.

1502
02:15:27,240 --> 02:15:30,720
I’m lucky you came into my life.

1503
02:15:32,040 --> 02:15:34,240
You’re so sweet, Berat.

1504
02:15:34,720 --> 02:15:35,720
You too.

1505
02:15:37,600 --> 02:15:40,880
I think it’s time to tell your mother about
our marriage.

1506
02:15:45,720 --> 02:15:47,119
But...

1507
02:15:47,120 --> 02:15:49,000
There’s no point delaying it.

1508
02:15:51,480 --> 02:15:53,200
Maybe if some time passed.

1509
02:15:53,920 --> 02:15:56,239
But her health looks good.

1510
02:15:56,240 --> 02:15:57,680
True.

1511
02:15:58,000 --> 02:15:59,280
Thank God, it is.

1512
02:16:00,320 --> 02:16:03,440
She’ll be happy about this.

1513
02:16:05,520 --> 02:16:06,520
You think so?

1514
02:16:07,040 --> 02:16:08,920
I do.

1515
02:16:19,840 --> 02:16:22,320
We’ll be a very happy family, Berat.

1516
02:16:23,360 --> 02:16:24,920
My Berat.

1517
02:16:25,440 --> 02:16:27,360
My lion.

1518
02:16:27,800 --> 02:16:29,080
My Berat.

1519
02:16:33,600 --> 02:16:34,400
My dear.

1520
02:16:34,560 --> 02:16:35,480
We’ll be very happy.

1521
02:16:35,481 --> 02:16:36,840
Yes, we will.

1522
02:16:38,160 --> 02:16:39,880
Zehra, okay, don’t overdo it.

1523
02:16:40,200 --> 02:16:42,720
Ateş, Mr. Haydar might see something.

1524
02:16:43,000 --> 02:16:44,000
Okay.

1525
02:16:46,800 --> 02:16:47,640
Come on.

1526
02:16:47,760 --> 02:16:49,080
Let’s get back to work.

1527
02:16:49,920 --> 02:16:50,920
So nothing happens later.

1528
02:16:51,040 --> 02:16:52,040
Okay.

1529
02:16:52,440 --> 02:16:53,440
See you.
Take care.

1530
02:16:54,120 --> 02:16:55,120
You too.

1531
02:17:05,960 --> 02:17:07,640
She said she fixed things with his mother.

1532
02:17:07,680 --> 02:17:08,680
She said soup.

1533
02:17:09,520 --> 02:17:10,520
She said she liked it.

1534
02:17:11,360 --> 02:17:12,440
She said marriage.

1535
02:17:13,280 --> 02:17:14,360
She said my lion.

1536
02:17:16,000 --> 02:17:17,240
I’m confused.

1537
02:17:21,360 --> 02:17:22,360
Whatever’s best.

1538
02:17:22,760 --> 02:17:24,200
May God grant us a good ending.

1539
02:18:37,480 --> 02:18:38,480
Ateş.

1540
02:18:39,280 --> 02:18:40,880
Look who I brought.

1541
02:18:58,360 --> 02:18:59,360
Monika?

1542
02:19:01,440 --> 02:19:02,440
Welcome.

1543
02:19:03,000 --> 02:19:04,800
No need for formality, Ateş.

1544
02:19:05,040 --> 02:19:06,120
It’s been a long time.

1545
02:19:06,200 --> 02:19:07,200
I missed you.

1546
02:19:12,280 --> 02:19:13,280
You’re right.

1547
02:19:13,400 --> 02:19:14,400
It has.

1548
02:19:17,720 --> 02:19:18,880
Welcome, sit down.

1549
02:19:21,400 --> 02:19:23,120
Aslı and I talk often.

1550
02:19:24,240 --> 02:19:26,240
We hear about you from her.

1551
02:19:26,840 --> 02:19:28,120
We never even call.

1552
02:19:29,600 --> 02:19:30,880
Are you in Istanbul for work?

1553
02:19:31,880 --> 02:19:32,920
No, my dear.

1554
02:19:33,280 --> 02:19:34,640
I came to see you.

1555
02:19:35,080 --> 02:19:36,680
I was in Athens for a long time.

1556
02:19:37,040 --> 02:19:39,040
Our company opened a branch there too.

1557
02:19:39,760 --> 02:19:43,040
When I completed my job, I didn’t want to
leave for America without seeing you.

1558
02:19:43,240 --> 02:19:44,240
You did well.

1559
02:19:45,200 --> 02:19:46,840
Everyone from school scattered.

1560
02:19:47,120 --> 02:19:48,400
Just you and me left.

1561
02:19:52,320 --> 02:19:53,520
Yes, that’s how it turned out.

1562
02:19:54,200 --> 02:19:57,120
Some bonds don’t break though.

1563
02:20:00,720 --> 02:20:02,159
I have something to take care of.

1564
02:20:02,160 --> 02:20:03,680
You chat.

1565
02:20:03,880 --> 02:20:05,320
I’ll be right back.

1566
02:20:17,880 --> 02:20:18,960
You haven’t changed at all.

1567
02:20:19,800 --> 02:20:23,320
Still serious, distant Ateş.

1568
02:20:27,400 --> 02:20:28,400
No.

1569
02:20:29,720 --> 02:20:30,920
I changed a lot.

1570
02:20:34,440 --> 02:20:36,400
Some things force you to change.

1571
02:20:41,240 --> 02:20:43,639
Aslı said you got married but...

1572
02:20:43,640 --> 02:20:44,640
I didn’t believe it.

1573
02:20:48,920 --> 02:20:49,920
I did.

1574
02:20:51,120 --> 02:20:53,440
You married the owner’s daughter.

1575
02:20:54,240 --> 02:20:56,080
A business deal?

1576
02:20:56,240 --> 02:20:57,600
Or a love match?

1577
02:21:01,080 --> 02:21:02,520
Wasn’t that a bit personal?

1578
02:21:29,320 --> 02:21:32,360
A bit too much.

1579
02:21:36,320 --> 02:21:38,120
This is better.

1580
02:21:43,120 --> 02:21:44,760
If she did it, you can too.

1581
02:21:47,520 --> 02:21:49,920
You can say this left side belongs to you.

1582
02:21:51,440 --> 02:21:53,000
You are my story.

1583
02:21:54,080 --> 02:21:55,080
My destiny.

1584
02:21:59,480 --> 02:22:02,120
No, that sounded too scripted.

1585
02:22:07,880 --> 02:22:08,880
Come on, Mercan.

1586
02:22:08,920 --> 02:22:09,920
Come on.

1587
02:22:13,560 --> 02:22:17,760
Still the same successful workaholic Ateş.

1588
02:23:11,040 --> 02:23:12,520
Who is this now?

1589
02:23:13,400 --> 02:23:14,400
Who?

1590
02:23:15,360 --> 02:23:17,600
We lived everything we shouldn’t have.

1591
02:23:19,000 --> 02:23:21,520
Instead of being good for each other...

1592
02:23:22,720 --> 02:23:24,720
we only hurt each other.

1593
02:23:28,720 --> 02:23:30,240
There was no other way anyway.

1594
02:23:54,840 --> 02:23:58,559
Just like we shattered everything else...

1595
02:23:58,560 --> 02:24:00,080
let this break too.
